Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.37,0:02:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The first principle we're talking about today, that nothing is causing anything.\NThe first illusion, the illusion that holds back most of the people in an audience such as this,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.21,0:02:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,in a world such as this, Chicago calibrates at 430, that is very advanced, relatively advanced intellect.\NThe thing that holds people back is the belief in causality,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.62,0:03:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the thought that something out there is causing, responsible for, blamed for, should be punished for,\Narrested and imprisoned, or thrown into hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.03,0:03:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Something is causing everything to happen.\NWe spend our lifetime looking for the culprits,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.68,0:03:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and that belief system is the very foundation of the Trial Lawyers Association.\NOur court system.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.63,0:03:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That something is causing something out there,\Nand all we have to do is find it, punish it, and life will get better.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.87,0:03:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's the world, you see how causality sets the world up into the duality of perpetrator and victim.\NBelief in causality sets up a perpetrator and a victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.54,0:04:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It creates endless contention and war.\NThe illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.36,0:04:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If something is causing something, it's based on an illusion because the intellect lacks humility.\NIt doesn't actually know at all why anything is happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.64,0:04:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Hasn't got the slightest idea.\NBut it can't handle that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.82,0:04:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So the child says to the teacher, why does the flower turn around and follow the sun?\NThe teacher says, heliotropism.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.70,0:04:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The child says, oh, he doesn't even know any more than he did before.\NNeither does the teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.10,0:04:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You still don't know why the flower follows the sun.\NSo the interjection of pseudo, pseudo-knowledge is the specialty of the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.76,0:05:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus we have creation versus evolution.\NBecause to explain how phenomena occur,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.27,0:05:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the explanation of evolution, you see, is causal.\NYou have the billiard balls, A, B, C, D, E, all hitting each other in a sequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.14,0:05:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Causality, as an explanation for the phenomena of the world,\Ncalibrates, in my vernacular, at a miserable 450 or 460.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.35,0:05:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Causality calibrates around 450, 455, 460.\NNewton's law of evolution calibrates around 450, 455, 460.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.13,0:05:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Newton's law of evolution calibrates around 450, 455, 460.\NNewton's law of evolution calibrates around 450, 455, 460.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.11,0:05:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Not Newton.\NWhat's his name? Darwin.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.44,0:06:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Darwin's law of evolution.\NBased on causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.15,0:06:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Causality on our calibrated scale of consciousness,\Nwhich we'll get to as soon as we have the machinery set up,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.15,0:06:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is the middle of the intellect.\Nis the middle of the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.36,0:06:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is the middle of the intellect.\NVery few people in our world ever transcend the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.67,0:06:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Very few people in our world ever transcend the intellect.\NThe intellect calibrates in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.67,0:06:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Spirit, love, the subjective reality of the world,\NThe intellect calibrates in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.56,0:06:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Spirit, love, the subjective reality of the world,\Nreally starts at 500, which is love.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.56,0:06:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,really starts at 500, which is love.\NThe other downside of the belief in causality
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.97,0:06:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is first of all it's dualistic.\Nis first of all it's dualistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.23,0:06:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So the pathway I teach, called devotional non-duality,\Nis to transcend duality,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.23,0:07:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is to transcend duality,\Nto transcend the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.88,0:07:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So long as you believe there's a this causing a that,\Nyou will believe that there is a separate self,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.04,0:07:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you will believe that there is a separate self,\Nseparate from the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.00,0:07:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There is an it,\Ncausing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.32,0:07:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This it should be guilty,\Nthrown in hell, punished,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.67,0:07:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,rewarded, worshipped.\NSo the belief in causality
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.06,0:07:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,anchors the belief in a separate self\Nanchors the belief in a separate self
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.06,0:07:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and anchors the idea,\Nthe reality of the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.06,0:07:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,as an actual it.\NIt's the it causing you to do all these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.83,0:07:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the it causing you to do all these things.\NAnd all kinds of spiritual pathways
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.31,0:07:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,are set up to destroy the it.\Nare set up to destroy the it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.31,0:07:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Vanquish the ego.\NVanish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.31,0:07:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Conquer it.\NIt's much easier to dissolve it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.82,0:08:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,by removing its structure\Nand then it falls to its own accord.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.23,0:08:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If things are not happening\Ndue to causality,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.23,0:08:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,if there is no it causing a that to happen,\Nthen how do phenomena occur?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.23,0:08:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Then how do phenomena occur?\NHow do they come about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.66,0:08:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,To understand better an analogy\Nto the reality of divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.66,0:08:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be\Ndivinity is like an infinite field
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.56,0:08:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of infinite power\Nwhose characteristic
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.59,0:08:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is more like gravity\Nthan anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.32,0:08:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Its power is infinite.\NIts domain is infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.51,0:08:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no beginning, no end.\NIt has no parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.31,0:08:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no opinions, no feelings.\NIt doesn't get angry at people.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.31,0:09:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't get angry at people.\NNot interested in vengeance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.52,0:09:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're not respectful of gravity\Nbe interested in vengeance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.77,0:09:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if you're not respectful of gravity\Nyou're in for difficult times.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.92,0:09:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so if divinity is infinite\NI just got cut out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.92,0:09:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you God.\NIf divinity is an infinite power
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.92,0:09:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,it's an infinite field\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.10,0:09:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll draw the infinite\Nwe'll draw God's picture this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.10,0:09:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,God doesn't mind, easy.\NSo God is actually this whole
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.10,0:09:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,field here, this entire board.\NHow's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.58,0:09:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,God is the infinite field.\NSo this is a giant electromagnetic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.58,0:09:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We're using this as a closer analogy\Nthan most of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.71,0:10:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,traditional religions.\NIn the middle of this infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.54,0:10:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,powerful field you have\Nthe ego, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.54,0:10:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,structure, see?\NWe're not having technical
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.28,0:10:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,successes this morning.\NHere we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.20,0:10:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,In the middle of it\Nyou have an ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.45,0:10:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It has some kind of form.\NIt's got belief systems,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.45,0:10:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,it's got structures.\NI was born in 1927
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.45,0:10:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,in Chicago, Illinois\Nand I'm son, this and this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.45,0:10:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's got definition.\NIt's got form.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.37,0:10:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So that which we call\Nthe ego structure then
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.37,0:10:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is form within an infinite\Nfield of non-form.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.52,0:10:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That door of this building\Nthis morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.52,0:10:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,An analogy to God.\NHere was this big
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.88,0:10:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,giant electromagnetic crane\Nout back here,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.88,0:11:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,whose power is infinite\Ncompared to the scrap metal
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.88,0:11:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,it's picking up.\NGuy throws the switch,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.94,0:11:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,tremendous power picks it up.\NNow, what happens
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.29,0:11:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to every little piece of scrap metal\Nfrom the tiniest to the largest
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.29,0:11:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,is completely at the effect\Nof the power of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.29,0:11:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't decide\Nwhere it's going to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.16,0:11:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not punished.\NThe electromagnetic is not punishing
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.16,0:11:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,this little ball bearing here,\Nbut zap, it's pulled right into the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.56,0:11:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So, over lifetimes then,\Nkarmically,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.61,0:11:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,what we acquire as a result\Nof spiritual intention then
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.09,0:11:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,are energy fuels\Nwith patterns within them
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.09,0:11:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,which becomes our karmic destiny.\NWe become like little
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.60,0:11:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,pieces of\Nlittle molecules of metal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.36,0:12:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a polarity\Nand we have a molecular structure
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.36,0:12:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is a composite\Nover many lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.52,0:12:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you have become now\Nis within this
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.52,0:12:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite field.\NIt's obvious that the field will
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.84,0:12:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,have complete influence\Nover the destiny of this thing
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.48,0:12:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,depending on how it changes\Nits own polarities
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.77,0:12:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and its own opinions\Nwhere it will go in the field then
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.57,0:12:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is now up to\Nthe content of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.65,0:12:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But the field is not going to change.\NThe field is not arbitrary.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.65,0:12:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,\Nas spirit leaves the body
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.71,0:12:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,where it goes, obviously,\Nis within the field
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.71,0:12:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,where it feels comfortable\Nwhere it's appropriate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.16,0:13:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Every human being\Nwhen they're first born
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.26,0:13:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,already has a calibratable\Nlevel of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.26,0:13:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The instant you're born\Nyou can calibrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.32,0:13:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Every newborn infant already has\Na calibrated level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.64,0:13:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Also,\Nthe moment of birth,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.51,0:13:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the exact moment of death\Nis already defined.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.51,0:13:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Not the means, not the how.\NThe exact moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.51,0:13:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have two interesting phenomena.\NNobody is born equal at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.16,0:13:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people are born with\Nconsciousness level 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.32,0:13:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,others 400.\NHow long we'll be
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.92,0:13:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,within a physical body is already determined.\NLet's see if what we said is a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.12,0:13:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask this.\NWhat I've just said is a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.12,0:13:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nin kinesiology what we do is
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.85,0:14:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,confirm things\Nthat are not within
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.85,0:14:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the ordinary belief system of people\Nand yet they answer
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.84,0:14:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,many questions and phenomena.\NBecause people who are
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.90,0:14:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Western world are unaware\Nof the whole phenomena of karma
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.03,0:14:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,are busy feeling sorry for themselves\Nand resentful all the time
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.41,0:14:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,because\Nthey don't see that everything
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.34,0:14:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is the result of an ongoing phenomena\Nover vast periods of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.88,0:14:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So things don't come about by\Ncausality.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.88,0:14:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no this causing of that.\NThen how do phenomena occur?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.36,0:14:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thing within\Ncreation then
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.60,0:14:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,has its potential.\NIt has its phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.18,0:14:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and its potentiality.\NAnd within the field of divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.30,0:15:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,its potentiality\Nbecomes an actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.64,0:15:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and unfolds.\NSo what you don't see is causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.96,0:15:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What you see is\Nthe ongoingness of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.22,0:15:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Creation is continuous\Nand unfolding.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.80,0:15:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And to the sequential\Nperception of the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.80,0:15:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,it looks like sequence.\NSequence then demands
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.09,0:15:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,an explanation cause causality.\NSo let's just look at how
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.02,0:15:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,a rose unfolds.\NThe rose within it
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.63,0:15:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,has a karmic potentiality.\NIt's born
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.63,0:15:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,with the potential\Nto become a magnificent
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.63,0:15:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,rose. But it's not\Na rose now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.69,0:15:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing can force it to become\Na rose nor can anything cause
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.76,0:15:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it to become a rose.\NBut under appropriate conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.04,0:16:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of the field, under the\Nconditions of the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.30,0:16:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it then begins to\Nfulfill its potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.30,0:16:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and present itself\Nas an actuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.30,0:16:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?\NIt's unfolding its potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.42,0:16:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is causing,\Nnobody here can cause
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.42,0:16:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,a rose to do anything.\NWhether a thing will manifest
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.24,0:16:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,its potentiality depends\Non local conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.36,0:16:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have\Nthat karmic potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.16,0:16:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You have reality.\NYou have the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.41,0:16:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And then manifesting\Ndepending on local conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.79,0:16:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, creation\Nand evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.95,0:17:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,are one and the same thing\Nin that you see
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.61,0:17:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that evolution is nothing\Nbut the unfolding of creation
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.64,0:17:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to perception.\NThere is no conflict
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.73,0:17:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,between creation and evolution.\NThey're identical.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.18,0:17:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that obvious?\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.36,0:17:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the field\Ntends to manifest
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.84,0:17:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the potential\Nof that which is within it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.16,0:17:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That was\Nan interesting example.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.92,0:17:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Even scientists\Nbegin to suspect
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.99,0:17:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that there's more than\Nthe linear domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.47,0:17:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Because in explaining\Nwhat happened to one of these
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.47,0:17:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,rockets where the\Ninsulation fell off or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.53,0:17:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Shuttle deal.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.95,0:17:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You see they started\Nlooking for causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.95,0:18:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They couldn't really find\Nthe answer in causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.08,0:18:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,They had some quasi examples\Nbut they didn't have
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.62,0:18:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,anything definitive.\NAnd finally they got
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.62,0:18:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and I saw it the other day\Nit says it's the climate
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.62,0:18:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of NASA that allowed\Nfor this to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.88,0:18:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The climate. Aha.\NThey breached certain
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.88,0:18:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,negligences or routine.\NIt's the climate. Aha.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.88,0:18:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The climate.\NIt's out of a climate
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.88,0:18:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that war arises.\NThis person doesn't cause a war there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.88,0:18:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's out of a whole climate.\NYou have to have a whole population.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.77,0:18:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The climate of a whole population\Nwilling to say
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.77,0:18:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,let's kill everybody\Nor let's chop up
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.77,0:18:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the other side.\NYou have to have a climate
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.77,0:18:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that can grow.\NJoseph Goebbels was
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.35,0:19:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,a great master of that.\NHe knew that it was fertile out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.35,0:19:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew how to fan the breeze\Nand get everybody inflamed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.41,0:19:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You see.\NSo you look there
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.76,0:19:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,where is the cause?\NWell you can't have a flame
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.76,0:19:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,without tinder.\NThere is the tinder.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.76,0:19:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,People willing to fan the flame\Nof war.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.21,0:19:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You see war isn't just a simple cause and effect.\NIt's a net effect of a total climate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.50,0:19:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A whole climate.\NAnd the climate of course changes with the times
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.50,0:19:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and the evolution of mankind.\NPolitical sophistication,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.50,0:19:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,education\Nand a thousand other things.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.85,0:19:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's my\Nfirst obligation
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.28,0:19:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to dissuade you of the\Ndevotion to the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.48,0:19:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,belief system of causality\Nbecause so long as
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.40,0:19:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you believe that\Nyou're reinforcing
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.40,0:20:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego constantly\Neverything we do think and believe
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.98,0:20:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is the manifestation\Nis like the consolidation
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.98,0:20:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of a whole field\Nwhich is evolved over great
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.98,0:20:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,periods of time.\NGreat periods of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.68,0:20:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see\Nthe evolution of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.68,0:20:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You look at the evolution of consciousness\Nof which I spoke last night a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.68,0:20:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,How many were here last night?\NOh quite a few.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.75,0:20:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember I said\Nin the beginning on this planet
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.75,0:20:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,there wasn't any life on this planet.\NSee if that's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.88,0:20:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to check that out.\NWe have permission to ask that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.74,0:20:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What could be called before the beginning\Nin the beginning?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.32,0:20:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no life on this planet.\NThere was life on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.32,0:20:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There was the potential for life on this planet.\NOh there was the energy of life on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.32,0:20:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There was the energy of life on this planet.\NThere was the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.98,0:21:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of\Ncoming out of the energy field of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.98,0:21:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,was the light\Nthe light of energy resist
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.98,0:21:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,as light resist.\NWe never asked that before.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.68,0:21:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In the beginning then\Nwe look back in history
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.68,0:21:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and we see that life forms were extremely primitive.\NAnd here were these primitive life forms
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.97,0:21:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,on a you might say\Nhostile planet
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.22,0:21:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in other words it wasn't necessarily\Nfriendly to life
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.38,0:21:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but life began to evolve then\Nby serving
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.60,0:21:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,itself.\NHere's a planet with no life on it
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.89,0:21:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,at that time that just the beginning of life\Nwas merely an energy
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.89,0:21:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,as yet no form.\NAnd as it begins to take form then
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.89,0:21:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,it has to find a way to survive.\NSo the first rule
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.89,0:21:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,of the emergence of life then\Nin the biologic domain
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.89,0:22:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,was survival.\NThat's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.77,0:22:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't introduce Susan.\NIt's because she's my right arm
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.16,0:22:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't feel like introducing my right arm.\NThis is my right arm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.16,0:22:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,She's become my right arm.\NShe's like one with the work
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.19,0:22:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,one with the work.\NSo we're asking things
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.19,0:22:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we never asked this morning\Nbecause we're always discovering
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.22,0:22:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,something new\Nor a new way of looking at things.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.25,0:22:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So then life began\Nin a very primitive form
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.35,0:22:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in which its survival\Nwas not at all guaranteed
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.35,0:22:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in fact quite unlikely in form\Nand so life then had to be
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.86,0:22:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,devoted to its own survival.\NYou see how
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.89,0:22:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,life then starts\Nin its most primitive forms
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.89,0:22:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,a germ let's say\Nand it's only interested
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.89,0:22:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in its own survival.\NIf we landed on Mars
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.34,0:23:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and decided to colonize\Nyou can see we would have one preoccupation
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.34,0:23:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is survival\Ngetting oxygen, food, water, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.34,0:23:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So life was obsessed then\Nnot obsessed but
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.60,0:23:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,as a matter of speaking\Ndevoted to survival
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.14,0:23:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,its survival\Nnot yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.97,0:23:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The bacterium under a rock\Nis not interested in the rock's survival
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.97,0:23:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,it's interested in its survival.\NSo life from the very beginning then
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.71,0:23:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is egocentric is it not?\NMe, me, me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.06,0:23:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the early life forms then\Nyou see the bug is interested
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.06,0:23:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in eating another bug\Nyou see the primitive life forms
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.06,0:23:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,are interested in eating\Nso life then
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.32,0:23:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,gets its\Nfoothold by virtue
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.60,0:23:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of eating you\Nso that I can survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.56,0:23:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This becomes extremely well developed\Nin the dinosaur
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.76,0:24:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,in the reptilian world\Nthe dinosaur is the ultimate
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.49,0:24:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,me\Ndoesn't care anything
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.65,0:24:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,lays an egg and walks away\Nnot much maternal instinct
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.29,0:24:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,don't even hang out to see if the eggs hatch\Nit takes off
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.29,0:24:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it's busy killing\Nand eating other people
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.52,0:24:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,such people\Nare still quite active
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.55,0:24:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,on our planet\Ninterested in killing other people
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.55,0:24:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,let's kill them\Nby the thousands
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.90,0:24:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,so the reptilian\Nthe dinosaur
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.16,0:24:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is still alive\Nso in fact
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.12,0:24:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the Komodo dragon calibrates\Nabout 70
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.12,0:24:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,so the Komodo dragon is a living example\Nof that
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.12,0:24:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,it is so deadly\Nit just bites you and walks away
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.12,0:24:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and waits till you die\Nit's perfected
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.08,0:25:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,really perfected\Nyeah
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.27,0:25:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,then we see life evolve\Nto higher forms
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.27,0:25:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't begin to see\Nthe evolution of love
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.27,0:25:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,until you really see\Nyou see the bird mother
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.68,0:25:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to pay attention to the eggs\Nhangs around
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.88,0:25:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the evolution of the mammalian\Nand the maternal instinct
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.88,0:25:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the appearance of love\Nthe consideration for something other than just my survival
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.88,0:25:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in fact\Nyou see in maternal love
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.88,0:25:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,risking their own survival\Nfor the life of the offspring
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.16,0:25:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you see the evolution\Non up through hominid
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.16,0:25:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,through Neanderthal man\Nwho calibrates around 75
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.20,0:25:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Cro-Magnon man\NPiltdown man
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.65,0:25:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,on up through the hominids\Ncalibrated around 70 to 90
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.65,0:26:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time of\Nthe birth of Buddha
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.10,0:26:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the consciousness level of mankind\Nas a whole
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.10,0:26:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,totality of mankind was 90\Ntotality of mankind was 90
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.55,0:26:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the consciousness level\Nof mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.93,0:26:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time of the birth of Jesus Christ\Nwas 100
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.04,0:26:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,so that was the audience\Nhe was speaking to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.04,0:26:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that calibrated at 100\Nlet's give some
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.08,0:26:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,depth to the field\Nof understanding his words
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.30,0:26:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,then over the centuries\Nthe 12th century, 13th, 14th
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.30,0:26:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,15th, 16th, 17th\Nif you calibrate all the centuries
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.30,0:26:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you find it calibrated\Nlevel 190
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.30,0:26:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,1600s, 1700s, 1800s\N1900s
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.30,0:26:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the time I was born 190\Nbecause
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.57,0:26:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity\Nand spirit of truth doesn't start
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.34,0:27:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,till calibrated level 200\Nthen the consciousness level
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.44,0:27:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of mankind was\Nnon-integrous
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.98,0:27:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,it was devoted to\Nfalsehood
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.17,0:27:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and the history of mankind\Nmakes sense
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.17,0:27:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,if you say well throughout the ages\Nthe consciousness level
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.17,0:27:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,during the dark ages was 190\Nnow
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.36,0:27:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the inquisition and all those things\Ndon't seem quite as despicable
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.36,0:27:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the reading\Nof the vikings
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.36,0:27:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the great hordes of the savages\Ncoming in the lombards
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.36,0:27:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and Genghis Khan and all\Nat 190
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.45,0:27:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the way consciousness\Nperceives survival
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.45,0:27:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is we have to kill you\Nto survive
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.60,0:27:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,then in the late 1980s\Nthe consciousness level jumped to over 200
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.60,0:27:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to 207\Nwhere it exists till this day
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.83,0:28:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,which means mankind now has a new\Nfuture
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.18,0:28:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,has new standards of conduct\Nthe field of 207 then
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.40,0:28:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,contextualizes\Nlife in a completely different way
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.67,0:28:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,than does consciousness\Nlevel 190
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.02,0:28:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level 190\Nin which I grew up
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.05,0:28:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,had to do with success\Nyou went to college to be a success
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.50,0:28:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,your parents said I hope you'll be a success\Nyou were supposed to be a success
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.56,0:28:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you were supposed to stay\Nas principled as you could
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.64,0:28:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but when it comes to giant corporations\Nyou have to bend that little bit
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.64,0:28:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to influence the stock price\Nso you can do your stock options
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.86,0:28:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,so\Nheads began to roll
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.86,0:28:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,so after it went to 205 then\Nor 207
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.44,0:29:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,where it is today\Nwhere is consciousness level today
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.66,0:29:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see\Nconsciousness level of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.30,0:29:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,we have permission to resist\Nis still at 207 resistance
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.30,0:29:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,went to 208\Nwell not yet
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.36,0:29:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,pray harder folks\N207
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.36,0:29:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,look at the vast amount of time\Nover which consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.55,0:29:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,then manifests as life\Nand then life evolves
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.55,0:29:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and it isn't until\Nthe late 1980s
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.71,0:29:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that it even gets over 200\Nwhich is the level
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.19,0:29:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,first level of truth\Non the calibrated scale of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.83,0:29:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,anything that calibrates under 200\Nmakes you go weak
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.83,0:29:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,anything over 200\Nwhich is truth
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.43,0:29:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,makes you go strong\Nuntil the late 1980s
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.52,0:30:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy field of mankind\Nof mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.64,0:30:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,made you go weak\Nso in a way that sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.05,0:30:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,recontextualizes history\Ndoesn't it
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.15,0:30:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you know\Ninstead of criticizing and faulting
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.15,0:30:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and putting down\Nwhat happened in the past
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.47,0:30:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you were doing what they thought\Nwas ethical
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.47,0:30:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you were supposed to get ahead\Nand be successful
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.47,0:30:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore that was\Nthe great world of materialism
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.98,0:30:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,materialism\Nsuccess, possessions, cars, address
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.98,0:30:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,how much money you were worth\Nnow the calibrated level
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.02,0:30:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,has reached 207\Nnow you see
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.02,0:30:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the level of integrity\Nso we see
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.08,0:30:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity then\Nand it's the beginning of empowerment
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.08,0:30:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,before that\Nyou see inflation and pride
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.37,0:31:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,so at 190\Nthe world was coming out
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.37,0:31:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of prideful indifference\Nto the rights of others
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.63,0:31:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so\Nwhen the Germans lost the war
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.88,0:31:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Adolf Hitler said\Nthey didn't deserve to live
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.01,0:31:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and he ordered that Germany\Nshould be destroyed
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.01,0:31:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Paris should be burned down\Nthe Eiffel Tower should be burned down
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.40,0:31:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you say that in that kind of a field\Nto us it would sound like insanity
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.40,0:31:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,because the field here\Nis probably 435 or so
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.40,0:31:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,so at 435\Nthat sounds like insanity
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.40,0:31:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,with the masses\Nwho are living down below
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.40,0:31:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can see\Nif the masses of humanity
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.40,0:31:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,are living down here\Nhow easy it is to control them
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.43,0:31:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,with falsehood\Nbecause their consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.43,0:31:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,is dominated by falsehood\Ngrief, apathy, threat
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.43,0:31:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,you can appeal to their desires\Nso it was the world
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.81,0:32:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of the solar plexus\Nwe grew up in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.81,0:32:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of the solar plexus\Nand we were angry
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.81,0:32:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and they got our way\Nand we were prideful of our accomplishments
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.99,0:32:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,so it was a different world\Nthan what we live in today
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.44,0:32:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,now we have a new paradigm of virtue\Nand that is as I spoke of last night
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.44,0:32:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity\Nthe courage to tell the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.44,0:32:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and to spill the milk\Nand I'll take care of it
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.56,0:32:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,get my check tomorrow\Nso I just wanted to first address
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.80,0:32:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the totality of the level of consciousness\Nof all of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.80,0:32:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,which is slowly evolving\Nand at the same time
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.80,0:32:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,take us beyond the polarity of good and evil\Nbecause
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.05,0:33:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,what should we say\Nall the bacteria are evil
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.05,0:33:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,because they are only interested in themselves\Nif you superimpose
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.50,0:33:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,on this phenomena\Nof evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.14,0:33:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,a moralistic code\Nyou can see how ridiculous it looks
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.75,0:33:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet that's what mankind has done\Nand traditional religion in a way
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.75,0:33:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,has done, reinforced\Nif we see that it is
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.24,0:33:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,critical for the establishment of life\Nto be self-interested
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.24,0:33:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,then you see how the ego\Nbecame so powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.06,0:33:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego became in its own view\Nthe source of survival
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.06,0:33:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and mankind to a degree\Nworshipped the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.51,0:33:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,when it didn't worship the ego\Nhe took its basic characteristics
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.67,0:33:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and projected them\Nanthropomorphically onto a god
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.67,0:33:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that was exactly like the ego\Nangry, jealous, spitful
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.73,0:34:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,punitive\Njudgmental
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.52,0:34:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,all you're talking about is the human ego\Nthat's the human ego
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.58,0:34:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to call it god\Nwith an E
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.58,0:34:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the capital E for God's ego\Nand a small E for man's ego
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.58,0:34:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,divinity would have to be\Nsomething devoid of
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.96,0:34:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the characteristics of form\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.19,0:34:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,what we call the ego\Nalright, so
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.28,0:34:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we don't usually start\Nthe lectures with that
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.40,0:34:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,but we did it today\Nbecause that's the way it happened
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.66,0:34:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the field\Nit's everybody's fault here
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.32,0:34:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,you made me do it\Nalright, so now you have
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.41,0:34:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,a more benign view of the ego\Nit's not an evil it
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.41,0:34:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have to battle\Nand struggle against
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.41,0:35:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and feel guilty about\Nyou don't have to wallow in guilt
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.41,0:35:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and penance\Nand self-flagellation
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.01,0:35:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,psychically or physically\Nyou see that the structure of the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.46,0:35:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is primarily animal\Nand it's interested in that
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.46,0:35:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,which an animal is interested in\Nsurvival, serving oneself
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.07,0:35:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and progresses\Nyou see the beginning of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.48,0:35:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,pack formation\Nloyalty
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.48,0:35:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the animal behavior\Nin competition for mates
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.48,0:35:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,for territory\Nterritoriality
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.92,0:35:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you see aggression in all of its forms\Nand so that's really the basic structure
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.71,0:35:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of the ego\Nis actually just an animal
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.19,0:35:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,alright, then as man learned to think\Nthen he
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.19,0:36:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,see man still has the animal structures\Nbut then along came the frontal cortex
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.22,0:36:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and now he could think\Nso what did man do?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.83,0:36:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,he still stayed an animal\Nbut now he's a thinking animal
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.99,0:36:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,he used to do it with teeth and claws\Nnow he does it with bombs and tanks
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.50,0:36:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing has changed\Nnow his intellect
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.59,0:36:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,he seeks to dominate other tribes\Nwith his intellect
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.10,0:36:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the democrats and the liberals\Nand all these people
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.10,0:36:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,are just an animal\Na talking animal
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.36,0:36:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,he did what it had fur\NI want your territory
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.60,0:36:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I want power over you\NI want you to follow me
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.60,0:36:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to join my pack\Nand like monkey island
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.86,0:36:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,they divide in\Nand they throw you know what at each other
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.86,0:36:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in monkey island\Ntypical political discussion
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.86,0:37:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah\Nas we said last night
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.46,0:37:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,as spiritual people\Nhow can we accept
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.46,0:37:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,what is and\Nit's because once you see that the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.07,0:37:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is nothing but a manifestation of animal nature\Nand that the intellect is merely an expansion of that
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.07,0:37:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you can get off good and evil\Nyou can get off good and evil
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.07,0:37:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's one of the most difficult\Nof all polarities to get off of
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.58,0:37:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you probably don't get off that duality\Nuntil about consciousness level 850
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.58,0:37:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see\Nyou transcend good and evil
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.58,0:37:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're over 800\N825, 840
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.58,0:37:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,850, 855\N860
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.38,0:37:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,alright so it's a very difficult\Npolarity
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.17,0:37:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,duality of the opposites\Nto begin to dissolve
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.44,0:37:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the demonization\Nof that which we call evil
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.86,0:38:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah\Nand to see it then
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.53,0:38:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,from a more forgiving and accepting\Nviewpoint without having to demonize
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.53,0:38:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,it and vilify it\Nbecause if you demonize it and vilify it out there
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.53,0:38:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you will do it\Nwithin yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.88,0:38:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you will do it against yourself\Nthose who do the course of miracles
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.26,0:38:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,know that forgiveness\Nis the ultimate answer to just about 99%
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.26,0:38:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,of every problem humans have\Nand the question is
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.45,0:38:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,how can you forgive something\Nthat looks dead evil
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.84,0:38:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,says the Holy Spirit will\Nrecontextualize it for us
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.87,0:38:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that's my languaging for what the Holy Spirit does\Nrecontextualizes it
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.87,0:38:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,so this morning what we've tried to do is\Nrecontextualize
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.87,0:38:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand the evolution of consciousness then\Nso we can witness
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.87,0:38:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that which we consider to be spiritually unfavorable\Nnot as evil
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.87,0:38:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,not as horrible\Nnot as something to beat ourselves about
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.03,0:39:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,or other people about\Nbut a natural consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.06,0:39:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of the evolution of consciousness\Nas it came up through
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.06,0:39:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and developed into form\Nhigher and higher form
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.06,0:39:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,began to express itself in the human\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.69,0:39:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,then it expanded its animal nature\Nand really used the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.69,0:39:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,as another tool of its animal nature\Nso you don't really
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.24,0:39:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,become man\Nin its true meaning with a capital M
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.72,0:39:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,until you begin to see\Nthat the mind has other uses
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.72,0:39:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,other than subserving animal instincts\Nsubserving animal instincts
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.55,0:39:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and a group\Nlike this has discovered that
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.80,0:39:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah\Nbecause here you've got
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.80,0:39:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,people in\Nadvanced in the 400's
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.80,0:39:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,discovered that\Nthe use of the intellect
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.80,0:39:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is to discover spiritual reality\Nand the ways to God
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.86,0:40:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and it has other uses\Nother than killing other people
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.86,0:40:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,for profit or fun\Nfor fun
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.86,0:40:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,alright so\NI'm going to go back to
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.91,0:40:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't talk about slide one yet\Nwe talked about slide one
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.35,0:40:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,as it is applied\Nbut we didn't talk about it
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.44,0:40:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's a more abstract viewpoint\Nthe development of the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.70,0:40:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated levels of consciousness\Nresulted as a consequence of
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.70,0:40:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,rather profound inner experiences\Nthat went on in this lifetime
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.70,0:40:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning in this life at age three\Nand becoming more
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.70,0:40:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,profound in teenage\Nand eventually through life
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.70,0:40:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,so that\Nwhen I saw
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.24,0:40:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,kinesiology for the first time\NI just merely understood it
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.24,0:40:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,from a different viewpoint\Nperhaps other people had
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.33,0:41:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,they saw it as a local phenomena\Nyou put the fig over your
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.33,0:41:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,stomach and if your arm goes weak\Nyou're allergic to figs
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.33,0:41:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,was sort of a very primitive\Nfirst application of it
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.43,0:41:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,so it saw it as a local phenomena\Nand tried to give a local
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.43,0:41:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,explanation\Nwhen I saw it
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.84,0:41:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw wow\Nthis is connection between mind and body
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.84,0:41:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and I saw that\Nwhat is answering the question is not
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.88,0:41:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the body at all\Nbut consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.88,0:41:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the body doesn't know anything\Nthere are books that tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.94,0:41:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,your body knows everything\NI got news for you
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.94,0:41:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,your body doesn't know anything\Nit's a complete idiot
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.44,0:41:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't ask my body anything\Nit's a stupid thing
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.44,0:41:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,what did I have for breakfast this morning\Nit doesn't say
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.92,0:41:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't know what I had for breakfast this morning\Ndon't look to the body for salvation
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.90,0:42:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it's there for fun\Npleasure
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.57,0:42:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a pet\NI discovered my body as a pet
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.57,0:42:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,because after I came out of a\Nstate in which
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.57,0:42:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind became silent and still\Nthe mind is still silent and still
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.08,0:42:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,if I listen to it now\NI don't hear anything
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.08,0:42:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't say anything\Nit doesn't think anything
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.66,0:42:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,it came into that state\Nand here is this body walking around
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.81,0:42:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it seemed to do fine by itself in space\Nthere's nobody running it
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.97,0:42:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no you running it\Nit's running itself
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.97,0:42:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't need you at all\Nyou see what it does by itself
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.97,0:42:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't need me at all\Nsee what it does by itself
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.60,0:42:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,it does it by itself\NI never know what it's going to do until it does it
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.45,0:43:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,wow\Nactually the body is a nuisance
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.99,0:43:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to me it's a nuisance\Nwhy people price it
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.99,0:43:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,it's always in your way\Nno matter what you want to do
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.99,0:43:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,your body is in the way to do it\Nyou've got to keep it there
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.92,0:43:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to park it someplace\Nthink what it costs you to keep this thing going
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.92,0:43:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a phenomena\NI'll be happy goodbye
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.40,0:43:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to drag it around every place\Nit's like luggage or something
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.40,0:43:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,so what I saw was\Nthe consciousness was
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.23,0:43:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,responding just as you saw\Nwith Susan this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.00,0:43:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the answer then\Nis that consciousness recognizes reality
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.00,0:43:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,anything that calibrates over time\Nthat which is below 200
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.37,0:43:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,then makes you go strong\Nthat which is below 200
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.08,0:44:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,which is fallacious\Nwhich has no truth
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.30,0:44:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not right and wrong\Nor yes and no
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.00,0:44:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the kinesiologic response is\Nyes and not yes
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.06,0:44:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,nature cannot answer with a no\Nit can answer with a yes
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.73,0:44:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,or it doesn't answer at all\Nso when our arm goes weak
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.73,0:44:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that's not a no\Nit's a not yes
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.24,0:44:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we have a slide here\NI don't know if we'll get to it
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.24,0:44:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,on quantum mechanics\Nconnecting quantum mechanics
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.40,0:44:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,with kinesiology and consciousness research\Nbut in line with quantum mechanics
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.16,0:44:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the theory of quantum mechanics\Nthe universe can only answer yes
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.22,0:44:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and it cannot answer with no\Nthrough the Heisenberg principle
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.38,0:44:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you can collapse the wave function\Nthrough consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.38,0:44:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's how we as spiritual people\Ninfluence the collective consciousness of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.38,0:44:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,as each one of us makes a positive\Nwe can collapse the wave function
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.38,0:45:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of potentiality into actuality\Nand actually change the field
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.38,0:45:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we actually have an influence on the field\Nso everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.96,0:45:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,praying quietly\Nevery forgiveness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.96,0:45:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,every act of kindness\Nevery time you see a little beetle
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.05,0:45:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have to just turn him over\Nso he can get on his way
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.05,0:45:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and give him a twig\Nso he gets a foothold again
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.05,0:45:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that changes the universe\Nevery act of kindness is noticed
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.60,0:45:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's true\Nscripture says every hair of your head
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.60,0:45:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,shall be counted\Nthat's an absolute fact
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.60,0:45:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,every hair of your head\Nis known and counted
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.60,0:45:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,not only is it known and counted\Nbut it's knowable and countable forever
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.60,0:45:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,within the field of consciousness\Nevery single thought
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.17,0:45:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling, decision, action\Nis registered forever
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.20,0:45:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,outside of time and space\Nbecause it is beyond form
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.30,0:46:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and time and space\Nit is indestructible
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.80,0:46:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,how can you destroy that which has no form\Nthe thing has to have form
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.80,0:46:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to destroy it\Nso that means that everything that ever happened
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.06,0:46:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in the history of the universe\Nis retrievable
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.06,0:46:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,now\Nin one instant
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.53,0:46:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,what Napoleon thought or felt\Nwhen he walked in the pyramid
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.53,0:46:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,what he thought and felt\Nwhen he walked out of the pyramid
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.91,0:46:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,how he felt about whoever his girlfriend was at the time\Nwhat they had for breakfast
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.96,0:46:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we used to check on Saddam what he had for breakfast\Nwhen we did these
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.96,0:46:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we used to check what he had for breakfast that morning\Neverything is knowable
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.96,0:46:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is knowable within an instant\Nthe only requirement is that the people
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.09,0:46:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,asking the question are doing so\Nfrom a position of integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.09,0:46:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,they themselves have to calibrate\Nover 200
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.32,0:47:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and the question itself has to be integrous\Nthat means your devotion
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.32,0:47:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is to the truth and not to\Nfinding some agreement
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.38,0:47:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to ask me\Nwhat about President Bush
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.00,0:47:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,there's also some idiot in the back\Nwhat about Saddam Hussein
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.12,0:47:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,so if you're looking to reinforce\Na belief system
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.76,0:47:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got your own ideas of good and evil\Nand then you want to use it to
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.76,0:47:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,prove what you already believe\Nthat's not the way you do science
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.76,0:47:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,you do science with no presumptions\Nto begin with
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.99,0:47:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you're devoted to the truth\Nbecause the pathway to God
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.08,0:47:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is through\Ntruth, absolute truth
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.71,0:47:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,devotional non-duality means then\Nto go beyond the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.71,0:47:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to transcend the ego\Nand one's devotion is to truth
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.93,0:48:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,so if the intention\Nof asking a question then
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.35,0:48:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is to discern what is the absolute truth\Nthen the results
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.48,0:48:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,are relatively accurate\Nthe test is done quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.96,0:48:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a very fast test\Nthe answer only lasts a few seconds
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.96,0:48:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you delay you won't get a\Ngood result
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.96,0:48:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,what you'll get is what I call\Nthe falling out of the tree recovery
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.05,0:48:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because the arm when it falls\Nin the primitive ape in you
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.05,0:48:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,think it's falling out of a tree\Nand it begins to try to right itself
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.37,0:48:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so you have to catch the response quickly\Notherwise the body will
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.92,0:48:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say a flash of weakness\Nit will begin to resist that weakness
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.92,0:48:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and it wants to hang into the tree\Nand not follow the tree
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.92,0:48:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so the trick is done very very quickly\Npeople ask us about it
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.92,0:48:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the technique we're telling you\Nyou use very little pressure
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.92,0:48:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you use very little pressure\Ntwo fingers and you press down
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.92,0:48:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and I say resist\Nand so I'm not using a lot of pressure
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.95,0:49:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and she's not pushing back\Nwith a lot of pressure
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.95,0:49:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you can do it delicately\Nso because I compare it with other things
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.95,0:49:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I can tell\Nso if I say a bear is a friendly animal
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.95,0:49:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,resist\Nsee it's a very quick response
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.17,0:49:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,a bear is not a friendly animal\Nhe can be taught to be semi-friendly
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.17,0:49:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,he can be taught to be semi-friendly\Nnot really friendly
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.33,0:49:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,he's good because he gets rewarded for being good\Nbut he's not really friendly
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.26,0:49:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,but he's not really friendly\Nas we said last night
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.26,0:49:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're in a spiritual despair\Nwhen you're in a spiritual despair
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.26,0:49:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got two little friends in the universe\Nready to rescue you
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.26,0:49:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,one is to know that a kitty's purr\Ncalibrates at 500
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.42,0:49:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and that a dog's wagging tail\Ncalibrates at 500
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.42,0:49:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,so those are two things I said last night\Nand I wanted to repeat them again today
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.42,0:49:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,how can it be that\Nthrough the evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.64,0:50:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that a kitty\Na kitty's purr is 500
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.25,0:50:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,where's our\Nsomebody keeps taking that off on us
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.25,0:50:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,every time we try that\Na kitty's purr is 500
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.79,0:50:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you know\Nlove
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.79,0:50:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a kitty's purr is 500\Nthe essence of love
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.88,0:50:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and the dog's wagging tail is 500\Na dog that just loves everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.88,0:50:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and makes friends with everybody\Nwho comes to the house
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.88,0:50:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,has to greet everybody\Nso instead of some long gone
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.06,0:50:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the statue of some long gone saint\Nwhen you're not feeling too good spiritually
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.06,0:50:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it's better to picture\Na purring kitty
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.06,0:50:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,get into the kitty's purr\Nbecause there you've got unconditional love
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.06,0:50:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,in the dog's wagging tail\Nso how is it that these two animals
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.25,0:50:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,bypass\Nsomething like 90% of humanity
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.34,0:51:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,90% of humanity\Nnever gets to be a purring kitty
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.34,0:51:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,or a wagging dog tail\Nthat's a curiosity
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.73,0:51:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,why that happened\Nalright
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.73,0:51:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,so on the calibrated level of consciousness\Nthen what we discovered was
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.73,0:51:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget how we started doing it\Nwe used kinesiology then
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.60,0:51:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we started using it\Nin abstract questions
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.60,0:51:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and things throughout time and space\Nwe did all the Greek atheism
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.76,0:51:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we did cathedrals\Nwe did countries
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.76,0:51:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,writers, authors\Nmovies we've calibrated
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.98,0:51:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,just about everything on the planet\Ncurrent book we've done 3000 calibrations
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.98,0:51:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're only half way through\Nif she holds up
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.08,0:51:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll finish the book\Nwell we do a run
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.04,0:51:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,when she's in the mood\Nthen she'll say I can't do anymore
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.04,0:52:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we did 100 movies I can't do anymore\NI know
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.40,0:52:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we found that then you could calibrate\Nthese are the classical levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.40,0:52:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,which have been traditional throughout the centuries\Nat the very bottom
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.88,0:52:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,we've got the very lowest\Nshame and guilt
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.98,0:52:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,apathy, grief\Nthen it comes up to fear
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.08,0:52:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,then desire, greed\Nanger, rage, hatred
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.59,0:52:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,pride, courage\Nthese make you go weak
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.45,0:52:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the domain of the ego\Nthis is where most people on the planet live
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.45,0:52:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,most of the time\Nand from a spiritual viewpoint
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.30,0:52:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,traditionally these have been condemned\Nnot only do you have this
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.91,0:52:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but you feel guilty about it\Nin case you don't
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.04,0:52:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the nearest church will inform you\Nyou should be doing penance
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.96,0:53:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,there's another way of looking at it\Nyou see the way to God is through joy
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.16,0:53:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,through happiness\Nand through truth
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.16,0:53:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not through self condemnation\Nanger, self pity
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.25,0:53:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,resentment and guilt\Ncrawling on your knees from here
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.28,0:53:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to the nearest cathedral\Nmay be impressive
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.39,0:53:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if it will make you enlightened\Nanother way of viewing these things
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.83,0:53:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,from a positive viewpoint\Nis each one of these is an improvement
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.83,0:53:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,over that which is below it\Nalright
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.28,0:53:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in the office they bring in a patient\NI've done psychiatry for 50 years
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.28,0:53:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,they bring in an old lady\Nwho sits there and rocks and won't eat
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.28,0:53:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,looks off into space\Ntake this pill mother
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.69,0:53:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it will make you feel better\Nshe just rocks and looks off into space
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.76,0:53:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,way down here\Nway down here
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.92,0:54:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,apathy\Napathetic
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.52,0:54:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,as we'll see later\Nif we ever get to the slides
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.64,0:54:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,whole continents live here\Ncontinents
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.71,0:54:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,not just individual people\Nwe'll show you continents
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.84,0:54:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that calibrate at 60\Nwhole continents
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.84,0:54:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,where the entire population\Nthis is where they calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.84,0:54:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,not enough energy to feed themselves\Nnot enough energy to control their
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.70,0:54:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,own behavior\Ndying right and left of AIDS
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.70,0:54:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and disease\Nand starvation
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.83,0:54:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and malnutrition\Nand infection
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.83,0:54:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and if they manage to survive\Na neighboring tribe will slaughter them anyway
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.92,0:54:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,average age of death 12 and a half\Naverage age of death in those countries
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.92,0:54:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,12 and a half\Nthe survival very slim
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.12,0:54:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,now\Nyou can see
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.04,0:55:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that we say fear is awful\Nbut you see
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.04,0:55:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,if you had the energy\Nenough energy to be fearful
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.04,0:55:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you could do something about the apathy\Nyou can run like hell
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.08,0:55:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in fear right\Nin fear you can build buildings
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.11,0:55:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,fortresses\Nif you're scared of starving to death
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.11,0:55:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it's amazing what you can do\Njust with your fingers
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.40,0:55:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it's bad viewed from here\Nbut viewed from here
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.40,0:55:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,this is a great improvement\Na major jump is to desire
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.43,0:55:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,when you get people out of apathy\Nso the benefit of television
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.43,0:55:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to the world is that\Ncultures that live down here in apathy
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.43,0:55:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,look on television\Nand they say
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.43,0:55:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,whoa look how those people live\Nyou begin to want something
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.43,0:55:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,so for them to awaken the solar plexus\Nis a major improvement
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.43,0:55:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,these people are down here\Nthey don't have the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.46,0:55:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to go to the bathroom\Nit's true
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.49,0:56:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,in a nursing home\Nthey don't have the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.81,0:56:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to go to the bathroom\Nso if you can get them up to fear
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.84,0:56:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,fear of starvation\Nfear of overpopulation
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.32,0:56:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,overpopulation\Nwill drive you into starvation
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.36,0:56:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to desire\Na higher level of living
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.71,0:56:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you get angry\Nthat you don't have it
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.16,0:56:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,anger then\Nhas a lot of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.22,0:56:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you can do a lot out of anger\Nand a lot out of desire
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.22,0:56:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and then pride\Nfeeds more energy back into it
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.99,0:56:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,so you enlist people into the Marines\Nbased on pride
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.02,0:56:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,but the Marines\Ndon't want you to hang out in pride
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.31,0:56:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,because people in pride\Nare a pain in the neck
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.50,0:56:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you want to get them up to courage\Npride gets you into service
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.50,0:56:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but courage is what it takes to face the enemy\Nso then
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.50,0:56:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you finally have launched over\Nfirst step in the 12 step program
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.50,0:57:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,this is\Nthe courage to tell the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.50,0:57:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the courage to tell the truth\Nthat without God's help
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.01,0:57:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it's unlikely that my consciousness\Nis going to evolve
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.56,0:57:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,much less become enlightened\Nwithout God's help
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.56,0:57:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm helpless without God's help\Nso you see weakness then
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.75,0:57:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,comes from the ego\Ndealing with the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.75,0:57:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and power comes from the field\Nand when this says
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.75,0:57:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I am myself and I'm unable to accomplish this\Nand I must turn to the field
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.75,0:57:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,well the power of the field\Nis infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.77,0:57:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,there's nothing the power of the field can't do\Nso as we surrender
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.19,0:57:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,our will to God\Nand ask God to
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.28,0:57:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we ask to understand God's will for us\Nnow we're invoking
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.76,0:57:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the power of the field\Nthe ego within itself
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.92,0:57:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is looking to its ego\Nand other egos
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.92,0:58:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,vote for me\Nbuy my product
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.08,0:58:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,fear my gun\Nwhatever it is
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.37,0:58:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,now we're invoking\Nthe power of the field
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.37,0:58:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,so as you begin to surrender\Nto the power of the field
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.24,0:58:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,when you fall overboard\Nin the ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.24,0:58:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and you give all this up\Nand you surrender to God
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.62,0:58:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly you find that you can float\NI was in the navy
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.62,0:58:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and a minesweeper\NI got swept off
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.84,0:58:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and all I had to do was float\Nwhoa
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.84,0:58:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in the Huangpu river of all places in Shanghai\Nwith dead bodies
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.97,0:58:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and God knows what else in the water\Nyou had to not think about that
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.97,0:58:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,but\NI floated along and what do you know
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.97,0:58:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,here was a warship\Nthey were docked side by side
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.97,0:58:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm carrying down this strong current\Nand here's the prow of a warship right ahead of me
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.97,0:59:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm headed right for this thing\Nand I just went like this against the prow
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.97,0:59:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and the water kept me there\Nand then they came and got me
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.97,0:59:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,so you see the power of the field saved my life\Nif I kept struggling I would have killed myself
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.23,0:59:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,so the power of the field\Nso our survival then
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.23,0:59:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is up to the field\Nso the ego claims credit
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.23,0:59:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,for our survival\Nbut the power of our survival
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.23,0:59:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is within the field\Nit's the field that decides
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.23,0:59:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to pull the chocks out\Nwhen the moment of physical death
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.23,0:59:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,arises\Nso there's a lot of good news this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.28,0:59:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,one is that the moment of your death\Nis already set
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.28,0:59:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can forget worrying about it\Nyou don't have to worry whether asparagus
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.28,0:59:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to shorten your life\NI mean it's not going to shorten your life
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.28,0:59:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,if it's death by a scary asparagus\Nthat's what it'll be
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.28,0:59:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody is so fearful in our society\Nand you know
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.34,0:59:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,science in the public interest\Nis something I was telling you
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.34,1:00:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,some new horror story\Nwhen you get out of the car
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.20,1:00:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you have a higher case of being killed in an accident\Nso everybody moves to the left rear
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.20,1:00:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,being on the highway in the first place\Nis a risk factor
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.20,1:00:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,so why are you driving if you're so scared of everything\Nyou've got to eat this
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.20,1:00:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,with kernels on it\Nyou get blocked in by all these fears
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.20,1:00:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and belief systems\Nbecause the ego is telling you
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.20,1:00:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to save you boy\NI'll tell you
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.20,1:00:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in the end it's not\Nthe other good news
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.27,1:00:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is that it's not possible\Nto experience your own physical death
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.27,1:00:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that is not a possibility\Nthose of you who have died
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.39,1:00:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and decided to come back in the body\Nare aware of that
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.22,1:00:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,how many people have had near death experiences\Nnot so many here
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.32,1:00:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway\Nthose who had near death experiences
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.32,1:00:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,those who calibrated over 600\Nand remember past lifetimes
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.32,1:01:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,remember that in one instant you're in the body\Nnext minute you're out and you're looking at it
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.50,1:01:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and there it is laying there\Nand you can't experience your own physical death
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.95,1:01:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,so I just thought\Nthat might be helpful
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.46,1:01:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,because so many people are afraid of\Nphysical death
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.49,1:01:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can't experience it\Nnobody can experience physical death
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.49,1:01:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,because the you is no longer there\Nand if it's not there
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.49,1:01:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,how can they experience what's there\Nwhen it's here
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.49,1:01:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,how many people here have gone out of body\Nout of body
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.49,1:01:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,more out of bodies than near deathers\Nok
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.49,1:01:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,well you know the instant you're out of body\Nthe you is up here
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.49,1:01:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and the body is down there\Nbut that which is me
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.49,1:01:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,is up here\Nthe me is up here
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.49,1:01:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the sense of self\Nme, I
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.20,1:01:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the focus of your existence\Nhas nothing to do with the physicality
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.20,1:02:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,because the physicality is laying down there\Nalright so
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.61,1:02:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the beginning of spiritual truth\Ncalibrates at 200
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.61,1:02:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the arm goes strong\None is empowered by truth
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.61,1:02:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond that\Nyou go to neutrality
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.64,1:02:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,courage is\Nyou still can feel fear
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.64,1:02:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in courage\Nyou can still feel fear
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.64,1:02:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but walk into the bullets anyway\Nand many a lifetime
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.64,1:02:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is often gone through\Nbefore one is finally
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.64,1:02:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,for a higher principle, a higher cause\Nwilling to face the bullets
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.12,1:02:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and actually die for the cause\Nand then they have conquered all of this
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.12,1:02:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond that\Nis a more comfortable level called neutral
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.18,1:02:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,neutral\Nit's ok if you get the job
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.18,1:02:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it's ok if you don't\Nwillingness is an even higher energy level
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.82,1:02:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,neutral she serves you your breakfast\Nshe takes your order in the restaurant
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.82,1:03:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but she doesn't really look you in the eye\Nwillingness is how can I help you
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.01,1:03:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,so we're getting closer and closer to Walmart\Nas we get up there
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.01,1:03:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,laughter\Nlaughter
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.49,1:03:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,laughter\Nwe did all the corporations in America
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.52,1:03:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you know\NI know there's Walmart haters out there
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.52,1:03:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and you'll have to forgive me\Nbut anyway
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.52,1:03:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,whether people like it or not Walmart calibrates\Nhigher than any corporation in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.52,1:03:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it is also the largest corporation in the world\Nit also has the biggest bottom line
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.52,1:03:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,so what's strange about Walmart\Nis that they
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.52,1:03:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,tend to be friendly\Nhow can I help you
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.52,1:03:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,if you don't like the product bring it back\Nwe give you your money
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.52,1:03:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so he bought the product\Non sale
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.88,1:03:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you were thinking it'd I\Nthe videos
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.88,1:03:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to\Nand it was
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.16,1:03:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,good\Nsome people
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.16,1:04:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but\Nwell
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.16,1:04:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,if you do\Nthem
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.16,1:04:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,make money\Nthere's no
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.16,1:04:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Calvary's higher than any corporation in the world.\NSo that's interesting, that spiritual principles,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.74,1:04:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,when they're applied to everyday life, are not airy-fairy.\NSpiritual principles of integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.18,1:04:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,are the most profoundly important thing in business.\NIt's integrity that shows up on the bottom line.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.20,1:04:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've got the example of Walmart.\NWalmart's the biggest corporation in the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.20,1:04:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole world, not just the U.S.,\Nand the most profitable, biggest corporation in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.20,1:04:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,based on spiritual principles.\NIsn't that marvelous?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.12,1:04:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's not exactly airy-fairy, airy-fairy.\NSo when people try to establish spiritual principles in business,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.84,1:05:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,don't call them spiritual.\NDon't call them spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.08,1:05:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Just say integrity pays off, and Walmart is a prime example.\NAnd we see Enron and those companies
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.54,1:05:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,where the opposite was applied.\NAll collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.42,1:05:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so the validity, then, of integrity\Nas the basis of everyday practical life.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.66,1:05:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we move on up to acceptance,\Nwhich is a very comfortable thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.10,1:05:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and reason and the intellect.\NSo America calibrates around 425, 431, around there.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.79,1:05:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the world of reason and the intellect.\NThat's also the reason of logic.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.22,1:05:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The intellect.\NThe intellect will take you as far as Einstein.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.10,1:05:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein calibrates at 499.\NSir Isaac Newton, who invented the differential calculus
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.85,1:05:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Newtonian paradigm of reality,\Nwhich is the home of causality, 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.69,1:06:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein, 499.\NSir Isaac Newton, 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.91,1:06:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Sigmund Freud, 499.\NSo that's pushing the intellect as far as you can go.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.24,1:06:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Pushing the intellect as far as you can go.\NWhat happened with Einstein,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.56,1:06:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,then, was at the Solvay Conference,\NCopenhagen, on quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.19,1:06:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem was facing the implication,\Nthe metaphysical, philosophic implication
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.65,1:06:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Heisenberg principle.\NThe discovery that on the microscopic,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.53,1:06:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,submicroscopic level,\Nthat merely observation already changes the result.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.87,1:06:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The introduction of human consciousness\Nalready changes the result,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.93,1:06:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,collapses the wave function,\Nand brings,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.69,1:06:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,out a new reality.\NSo the potentiality becomes an actuality,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.86,1:06:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and the trigger is merely human observation.\NAt that time, there was all the big leading people,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.01,1:06:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, theoretical physics, Bohm,\Nand all the people there.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.06,1:07:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And Einstein said,\Nyou see, what we're talking about is a paradigm jump.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.49,1:07:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein said, I prefer to think.\NThere's an observable, verifiable, objective world
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.72,1:07:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that exists.\NIt exists independent of human observation.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.76,1:07:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Independent.\NAnd at that point, he sealed himself off at 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.82,1:07:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the jump to 500 is a different paradigm.\NThey are jumping from the objective to the subjective.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.95,1:07:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,See, love is subjective.\NYou can't prove love.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.91,1:07:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't measure love.\NSo the scientific dictum that if you can't measure it or weigh it,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.07,1:07:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it isn't real, you know, is idiotic, right, on the surface.\NBecause that's a subjective concept.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.65,1:07:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a subjective conclusion on the first place.\NIt's radical subjectivity to assume that some proposition is true.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.67,1:08:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So the beginning of spiritual reality, as we understand it,\Nit calibrates 500 and up.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.91,1:08:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The world of the kitty purr.\NThe domain of the wagging tail.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.97,1:08:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The domain of the wagging tail.\NRare is the individual in our world who calibrates at 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.14,1:08:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.\NFour percent.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.80,1:08:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Four percent of humanity calibrates 500 or over.\NFour percent of all the people on this earth ever get to consciousness level 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.45,1:08:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Love at 500 is still conditional.\NSo the dog will love just about everybody, but occasionally he won't.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.41,1:08:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a little bit conditional.\NOtherwise, he'd calibrate at 540.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.13,1:08:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,540 is unconditional love.\NThat's interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.80,1:09:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Unconditional love, then, is practically saintly.\NIt is, oddly enough, 540 is a calibrated level of AA and all the 12-step programs.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.70,1:09:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Unconditional love.\NA guy in AA goes out and gets drunk.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.95,1:09:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He drives over four people, destroys his car, burns down the house.\NHe goes back to a meeting, and they say,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.49,1:09:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,George, we're sure glad you're back.\NNow, only one concern.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.46,1:09:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's this man's spiritual recovery.\NPeriod.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.56,1:09:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All the rest.\NThey leave for the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.04,1:09:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And A Course in Miracles, of course, calibrates at 600.\NSo 500 is extremely rare.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.92,1:09:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,540, 0.4% of the world's population ever reaches 540.\NBy 570, we consider them saints.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.11,1:09:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Father Pio, all the great spiritual writers, Dalai Lama, the Pope, all those people are in 570, around in there.\NWe consider them saintly.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.70,1:10:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,To transcend saintliness, then, is another dimension.\NAnd it takes one to 600, in which the mind is transcended altogether.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.56,1:10:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything becomes silent, beatific.\NOne is outside time, space, dimension, position.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.20,1:10:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And the body is irrelevant.\NAnd if the world and karmically...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.02,1:10:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Karmically is actually a karmic inheritance.\NIf the body is destined to continue, then friendly...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.94,1:10:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,People and supportive beings will appear that encourage you to hang into the body, and feed it, and clothe it, and all kinds of things that they seem to be interested in.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.71,1:10:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, 50% of the people, once they hit 600, will leave the body.\NAnd if you've ever gone to a bliss state, you realize how easy that would be.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.52,1:10:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've been in a divine state, you know that whether it continues or not is irrelevant.\NBecause the experience...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.48,1:11:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The experience is beyond physicality, and one loses one's interest in the world of appearance, huh?\N600 is extremely rare.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.10,1:11:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,One in 10 million people, huh?\NThe other odd thing that happens at 600...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.32,1:11:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, not really quite at 600, but 600 or over, is the recall of past lives.\NThere's no longer identification with this physicality or the mind, because you think...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.65,1:11:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,When you think my life, what you mean is...\NThe memory of this body, and this fixed quantum of mentation, when you stop identifying with the physicality and the mind, when you're beyond mind and body, then all the lifetimes are one lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.34,1:11:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And significant events happen in each one of profound spiritual implication, and those you remember, because they were powerful lessons.\NThat's why...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.88,1:12:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That life went that way, was to learn that lesson, to learn that you are a spirit, for instance.\NSo, at the oars of a slave ship, in a state of agony and semi-starvation and dehydration, in a stench that's unbelievable, under extreme cruelty, you suddenly get, you don't have to be trapped, you're not a prisoner, you can just leave the body and die.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.44,1:12:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Wham!\NOut of body.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.42,1:12:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of body.\NHa ha ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.00,1:12:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You thought you were caught in an endless torture chamber.\NHow stupid.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.34,1:12:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you realize that you could just let the body die, and you're free of it.\NHuh.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.53,1:12:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell old people that in the nursing homes all the time.\NThey call me in, tell them it's okay to die.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.81,1:13:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You know.\NI was the psychiatrist for all the nursing homes in the county, because there wasn't any other psychiatrist who's willing to do it, to go and see all these old people.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.30,1:13:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And they'd be going back to the nursing home, and they'd be saying, here's the body.\Npeople going back and forth in a wheelchair,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.62,1:13:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,help, help, help, help.\NAnd I look at her and I say,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.96,1:13:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Granny, what's the matter?\NHelp, help, and you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:12.40,1:13:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,they won't let me die.\NIt's against Medicare regulations
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.76,1:13:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to let a patient die.\NShe wants to please pull all these tubes out
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.17,1:13:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and let me be in peace, you know?\NJust as she goes off in peace,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.79,1:13:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,they stick some more tubes\Nand pump some more things in her
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.21,1:13:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and force her to keep breathing and yeah, so.\NAll right, so then the higher levels of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.97,1:13:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,of course, are traditional throughout history\Nand they're extremely rare.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.93,1:13:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of those people do not stay around.\NThose who reach like 700 and on
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.47,1:13:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,seldom become teachers or anything.\NThey usually withdraw from the world
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.91,1:13:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,if they continue to exist.\NAnd rarely do they come to the attention of the world
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.15,1:14:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and the ability to speak, the ability to speak.\NAnd when such a state comes on,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.32,1:14:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it's necessary\Nto really leave the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:06.46,1:14:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way you can relate to the world.\NThere's nothing you can say about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.43,1:14:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way to describe it.\NThere's nothing to describe.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.48,1:14:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The profound change cannot be communicated.\NSo usually nothing is said about it at all,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.70,1:14:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,except through accidentally getting dragged back\Ninto the world to speak of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.88,1:14:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So those are the ineffable states.\NThe transcending of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.46,1:14:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So today we want to really address that more intensely.\NFirst, we have sort of a map of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.76,1:14:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to tell us where we're going.\NAnd let's go on to the next one then.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.02,1:14:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to show the distribution of the levels\Nof consciousness in mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:52.38,1:14:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So the population of the world,\Nthis is the population of the world, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.86,1:15:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,To reach 1,000 is, one person to 1,000 is,\Ncounterbalances the entire negativity over here.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.87,1:15:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,200 or one or two at 700 counterbalances\Nthe total negativity of all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.11,1:15:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Two or three here counterbalances all of mankind.\NBecause you see, here's the world's population,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.85,1:15:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 200, but less than 200.\NSo the great mass of mankind then,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.09,1:15:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the mass of mankind is here.\NHere's where most Americans live,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.94,1:15:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,where an audience like this lives right about in here.\NAnd you see how few in number they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.25,1:15:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But collectively, the people in this realm\Nare also counterbalancing the negative.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.49,1:15:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if it weren't for those\Nof a higher level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.80,1:16:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see that the world's population would self-destruct.\NBecause the power of these people though,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.00,1:16:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,see these calibrated levels are,\Ndecimal, I mean are logarithm to base 10.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.66,1:16:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,These are logarithmic.\NConsequently, the increase of one point here,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.40,1:16:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is quite sizable because it's the logarithm\Nof going up to the base 10.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.38,1:16:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the power of these people is so enormous\Nthat they can counterbalance the mass of these people.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.28,1:16:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,These people are massive in number,\Nbut they are deficient in power.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.16,1:16:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So, only a few individuals then,\Nwho are spiritually evolved,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.36,1:16:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,are already counterbalancing huge numbers of people\Nat the other end of the spectrum.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.82,1:16:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the next one?\NAh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.36,1:16:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We were talking about duality,\Ntranscending good and evil,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.90,1:16:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,which is a very difficult one.\NTo understand how the ego works then,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.28,1:17:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it adopts a positionality.\NIt takes a position about something,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.88,1:17:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and once you take a position about something,\Nyou've now divided the world into the opposites.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.06,1:17:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The polarities of good and evil,\Nhot and cold, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.94,1:17:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,As we tried to explain early this morning then,\Nby seeing it differently,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.71,1:17:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you can transcend the opposites\Nand see that there are no such things as opposites,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.65,1:17:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that there's actually only one variable.\NAs an example, let's take hot and cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.53,1:17:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,People say, well, hot and cold are opposites.\NWell, if we put them all on the same scale,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.21,1:17:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll see there are not two opposites of hot and cold.\NThere's only the presence of heat or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.99,1:17:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one variable.\NAnd that is the presence of heat.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.46,1:17:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Get lots of heat, we call it hot.\NAs the heat goes down, the temperature goes down,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.05,1:18:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're not into two opposites now.\NHeat is not the opposite of cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.51,1:18:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is not its opposite.\NThis is merely a designation for convenience.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.75,1:18:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one variable present.\NIn all dualistic seeming polarities,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.58,1:18:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,there are not two opposites.\NThere's only one variable.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.62,1:18:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you see the one variable,\Nyou realize you can dissolve the so-called polarity
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.92,1:18:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of the opposites, which is the great blockade to enlightenment.\NClassically, the great blockade to enlightenment is getting stuck
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.50,1:18:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in the polarity of the opposites,\Nseeming polarity of the opposites.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.44,1:18:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll use another system.\NYou say things are good and things are worthless.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.28,1:18:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Things are good and bad and awful.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.11,1:18:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We skipped that one in a hurry.\NOn this one, we've got varying degrees of love.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.15,1:18:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NYou want to do that one?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.15,1:18:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care.\NHere, you have desirability.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.52,1:19:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, there's only one variable.\NAnd we value a thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.56,1:19:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one variable, and that's our desire for that thing.\NThings are not good and bad, desirable and repulsive.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.40,1:19:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You either desire them or you don't.\NYou may consider swallowing the entrails of a spiny creature
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.90,1:19:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,at the bottom of the sea, whether that's a delicacy\Nor repulsive.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.40,1:19:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Depends on your viewpoint.\NWhat was that spiny black thing at the bottom of the sea?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.21,1:19:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The black, spiny thing?\NWhatever it is, anyway, some parts of the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.68,1:19:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,swallowing its intestines is a great delicacy,\Nand it makes other people nauseated to think of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.44,1:19:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So, is it precious, valuable, worthwhile?\NShould we pay a lot of money for it on our sushi dinner
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.16,1:19:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,or whatever you call that?\NOr is it repulsive?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.26,1:19:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, okay, let's go to the next one.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.48,1:20:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the next one, we have the presence of love or not, see?\NIt's either there's the presence of love
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.14,1:20:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,or there's not the presence of love.\NThere either is love or not love.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.65,1:20:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,On the right-hand side, you see there are not opposites\Nof light and darkness.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.89,1:20:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are not opposites.\NSee, we're showing you how to transcend good and evil,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.49,1:20:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the tough one, but once you see the paradigm here,\Nyou'll see light is present or not present to varying degrees,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.13,1:20:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,but there isn't a thing called light.\NThere's no light against a thing called darkness, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.53,1:20:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see there's only one variable, light.\NThere's lots of it or not so much of it,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.68,1:20:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and lots of it.\NSo, we turn the light down.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.42,1:20:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, so there are no real opposites.\NYou see, because we give language to a thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.19,1:20:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,we think it must exist in reality.\NThat's the problem of the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:53.93,1:21:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why one can't become enlightened through the intellect,\Nbut only by transcending the intellect,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.69,1:21:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,because the intellect will always, you know,\Npropose something and then project it in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.73,1:21:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and think that it exists in the world.\NIt, you know, causality is an explanation.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.43,1:21:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a mentation.\NIt's an intellectualization.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.53,1:21:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It exists only as a mentalization.\NNobody can find any causality in the universe anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.86,1:21:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't exist out there.\NIt's a concept projected onto, okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.12,1:21:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an important jump in consciousness\Nbecause there you shift paradigm
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.97,1:21:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,from form and structure,\Nwhich is the limitation of the ego in the 400s,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.84,1:21:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and you begin to move into subjective reality\Nbecause the absolute reality that people are looking for
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.60,1:21:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,in all spiritual work is completely subjective.\NThat's why theology calibrates in the high 400s.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.18,1:22:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Theology will take you through the 400s,\Nphilosophy and theology, and the answer is the conundrums.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.46,1:22:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I have all the great books\Nof the Western world at home.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.56,1:22:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They calibrate around 465.\NThe answer to the enigmas of existence
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.34,1:22:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and divinity cannot be found through the intellect.\NThey can be talked about.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.26,1:22:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So theology calibrates around 465.\NLet's see if that's so.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.38,1:22:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask that here.\NTheology as a science calibrates over 460, 465, 470, 480.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.66,1:22:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, epistemology calibrates over 475, 480.\NEpistemology, hmm, well, the answer is that theology,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.78,1:22:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, philosophy takes you into theology,\Nand then theology, you hit dead ends,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.89,1:23:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and the answers then take you into epistemology.\NEpistemology is how does man know in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.83,1:23:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we know?\NBecause the riddles that have baffled the world
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.47,1:23:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,are the ones that are the most important to us.\NOkay?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.63,1:23:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They baffle the philosophers over the centuries, you know.\NEventually, you run up against,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.31,1:23:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,well, how do we even know anything?\NHow do we know that anything?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.47,1:23:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we know that we know?\NThen that is the question of epistemology.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.25,1:23:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We see it calibrates around 475.\NOf course, the answer is really by revelation, subjectively.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.89,1:23:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how you transcend to the next paradigm.\NYou have to leave the intellect altogether.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.10,1:23:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to, you cannot prove the kiddies' fur.\NYou cannot prove the doggies' wagging tail.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.18,1:23:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot prove love and compassion.\NYou cannot prove why you stop and turn a little beetle
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.32,1:23:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,over on his feet so he can get going again\Nbefore the sun comes out and shrivels him up.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.79,1:24:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you suddenly care about that little black beetle?\NActually, you don't really care.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.26,1:24:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't that you care about it,\Nbecause that's an attachment.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.24,1:24:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that that's the kind of being you have become.\NSo 500,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.71,1:24:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what love really means then.\NLove is not an emotion.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.71,1:24:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes from here to there, from me to you,\Nand therefore it's vulnerable.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.91,1:24:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If love is just an emotion,\Nthen you end up with homicide and suicide.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.85,1:24:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the setup, isn't it?\NIf it goes from here to there,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.74,1:24:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,well, you don't own it, now it's vulnerable,\Nand the other person can say bye now,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.04,1:24:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,then you have to kill them.\NOr whoever persuaded them to leave you,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.64,1:24:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to kill them both, better, you know?\NAnd at the end of that, you have to kill yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.32,1:24:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So that, there's the whole human tragedy\Nwithout which we couldn't have any operas.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.82,1:25:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We go to all the operas and watch all the,\Nwe love you, sweetheart, out there,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.46,1:25:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and then they go through the agony and the jealousy\Nand then they all stab themselves, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.80,1:25:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the curtain comes down, dun, dun, dun, dun.\NEncapsulates.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.63,1:25:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the whole human tragedy, yeah.\NNow, what happens as a result of spiritual work,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.31,1:25:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, and dedication,\Nis that you become the love of lovingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.40,1:25:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, love is a way of being.\NIt's what you have become.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.96,1:25:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not what you do, it's not what you feel,\Nit's what you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.56,1:25:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of what you are,\Nyou turn the little black beetle over, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.18,1:25:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't that you love them, and if you get squashed,\Nyou're not gonna grieve.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.62,1:25:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you might.\NYou might be a little black beetle,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.48,1:25:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but then you catch yourself emotionalizing about it,\Nand you disconnect from that, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.00,1:25:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So then, love is not an attachment,\Nit's a way of being in the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.24,1:26:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,a way of being in the world.\NIt's a necessary part of the evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.86,1:26:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to become enlightened,\Nbecause the ultimate realization is God is allness,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.41,1:26:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the allness of God.\NIt's important to see that at this point, because,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.94,1:26:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it's important to see that at this point, because,\Nit's important to see that at this point, because,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.98,1:26:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,there are certain branches of Buddhism,\Nwhich I am at liberty to speak of having been there,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.86,1:26:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,they will teach that love is another attachment.\NNow, emotional love as an attachment is a hindrance,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.59,1:26:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,but love as a way of being, then,\Nlove is one of the attributes of God,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.03,1:26:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you negate the divinity of love,\Nyou end up in the void,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.79,1:26:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and I've been in the void, it's very, very impressive.\NAnd if the void was real,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.60,1:27:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't be here to tell you about it.\NThe void is not the ultimate,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.11,1:27:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the pathway of negation, negation then,\Nhas a zinger in it, you gotta watch it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.22,1:27:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,God is the infinite allness of existence.\NOut of the unmanifest arises the manifest,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.83,1:27:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,arises consciousness, arises all of creation.\NGod is the allness out of which all arises
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.74,1:27:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and has its existence.\NYou know, I understand the void,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.46,1:27:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the void calibrates about 900 and something or other,\Nand it is extremely impressive,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.32,1:27:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,except you can't stay there.\NAnd then you come back the next lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.86,1:27:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,still in the void of nothingness, bang,\Nsuddenly confronted with existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.97,1:27:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You still haven't handled it.\NYou're not beyond existence versus non-existence
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.65,1:28:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is the ultimate reality.\NAnd that's where this lifetime started at age three.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.59,1:28:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of oblivion, absolute oblivion,\Nvoid, nothingness, suddenly there was a shock.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.88,1:28:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Like out of the darkness,\Nall of a sudden all the light's going on,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.71,1:28:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm shocked with existence.\NA three-year-old doesn't know the word existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.18,1:28:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't think existence.\NBut the knowingness of existence as existence
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.64,1:28:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,was like a shock, profound confrontation.\NI was not happy with it either.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.58,1:28:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I was not happy with being confronted\Nwith existence at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.60,1:28:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I voided it out, and here I am confronted with it again.\NAs soon as existence was faced as an experiential reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.24,1:28:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,it was an experiential reality.\NInstantly the fear of non-existence came up.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:57.37,1:29:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If you exist, it could have come about\Nthat you would not have existed.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.64,1:29:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And so there was the duality of existence\Nversus non-existence as the ultimate reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.58,1:29:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Another conundrum, the Calvary said 850 to resolve,\Nand it took 50 years to do it, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.61,1:29:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's interesting how life starts right out\Nwith the unfinished spiritual business that you're left with.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.86,1:29:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like it's the confrontation of the next life, huh?\NAll right, so we've handled now
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.06,1:29:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the most difficult dualities to be faced,\Nand we handled them early in the game instead of late.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.84,1:29:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And the reason we did is we wanted to take their structure\Nout from underneath them.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.18,1:29:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The structure is the belief that things are the opposites\Nof each other, which is not a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.42,1:30:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a mental positionality, yeah.\NThere's only one variable.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.64,1:30:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so now we've handled good versus evil and existence\Nversus non-existence, so as you get close to the door
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.82,1:30:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of enlightenment, these will not come up and hit you.\NOkay, we'll go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.13,1:30:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, yeah.\NThe mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:19.87,1:30:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We said it's based on positionalities,\Nand it tends to become enamored of itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.89,1:30:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The interesting thing about the mind, people say,\Nwell, to become enlightened or to become very spiritually evolved,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:34.25,1:30:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it's necessary to transcend the mind,\Nfirst to educate the mind about spiritual matters,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.02,1:30:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,but eventually you realize you're confronted\Nwith having to transcend it all altogether.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.78,1:30:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And the mind is structured then on certain positionalities,\Nand we tried to talk about the dualistic,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.38,1:31:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,polarities which are traditionally the blocks\Nto enlightenment, how to transcend the mind itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.83,1:31:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we learned a lot of interesting things this morning.\NThe next most interesting thing, and all the things
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.31,1:31:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that I tell you are gratifying and things to make you happy,\Nso you'll be real happy on the way home,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.31,1:31:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is that 99% of your mind is already silent.\NYou will think, how am I going to quiet this mind?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:21.06,1:31:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I meditate and it just chatters on and on.\NNinety-nine percent of your mind, or is it 98%?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.86,1:31:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Ninety-nine percent.\NUh-oh, is it 98% or 99%?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.14,1:31:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Ninety-nine percent.\NOh, I wrote 98%.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.38,1:31:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, 98% of your mind is silent.\NNow, you think when you listen to your mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.46,1:31:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're meditating and it's thinking about this,\Nimaging that, remembering that, and anticipating that,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:50.90,1:31:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can't seem to get your mind to be silent,\Nand people become very frustrated and they give up meditation,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.70,1:32:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's very frustrating.\NAll I do is just sit there and think my thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:02.34,1:32:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,which I do anyway when I'm driving,\Nso I'm wasting time and I'm not going to be a good Buddhist anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.30,1:32:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't like fish, and I don't like hamburgers,\Nand I like killing bugs, so I'm a lousy Buddhist, give up.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.98,1:32:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can become a Unitarian or join Unity, it's coming.\NSo, what is going on?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.49,1:32:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,This seeming horror.\NIt's a horrible block to enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.77,1:32:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What is going on with this?\NAnd there are all kinds of tomes and great establishments
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.55,1:32:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,dedicated to meditation and meditation techniques\Nwith fancy sounding names, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.47,1:32:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact is, if you look at mind,\Nif you look at your mind right now,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.61,1:32:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I will tell you one fact about it.\NNinety-eight percent of your mind is already silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.63,1:33:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Only one or two percent of your mind is thinking at all.\NWhat's happened is that you're focused on this one or two percent.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.74,1:33:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you're in a giant empty auditorium,\Na giant stadium.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:10.32,1:33:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Only one or two percent of your mind is thinking at all.\NWhat's happened is that you're focused on this one or two percent.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.60,1:33:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you're in a giant empty auditorium,\Na giant stadium.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:23.10,1:33:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's gone home.\NYou're the only one there, and way over in the corner,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.84,1:33:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got a four-by-five-inch old black and white TV,\Nand you're glued to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.60,1:33:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the only action.\NThere's nothing going on around here.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.78,1:33:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you say, boy, this is a noisy stadium.\NThere's no noise in the stadium.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.86,1:33:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that you're glued to this little four-by-five-inch\Nblack and white TV set.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.32,1:33:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so now I'll give you another secret truth,\Nand that is that you're hypnotized by the one percent.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.74,1:34:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Ninety-eight percent of your mind is silent,\Nand I'll demonstrate it to you this morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:02.34,1:34:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Only one or two percent is active,\Nand what's happened is that you're the hypnotic victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.78,1:34:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You have become hypnotized, and you're in a hypnotic state\Nof this one or two percent,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.95,1:34:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in a hypnotic, post-hypnotic state of suggestion\Nin which you think that you are the one percent that's going on
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.23,1:34:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's the only program on the dial.\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.51,1:34:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,.\NTo merely know that, certain knowledge advances consciousness rapidly just by hearing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.22,1:35:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Just to know that you are not the victim of your mind, that 98% of your mind is silent.\NAlright, so to know that you are merely in a hypnotic state.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.64,1:35:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This hypnotic state then is of the 1% that's going on in the corner,\Nwhich you then tend to identify with because it's the only program going on in this empty stadium.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.41,1:35:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We tried to take apart causality this morning because that's going to become critical to know when you want to transcend mind.\NThe mind thinks that one thought is causing another.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:36.42,1:35:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the mind thinks...\NThe mind thinks that...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.57,1:36:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The thought dog chases cat up and then the tree.\NNow, because it believes in sequential causality, it thinks that each one of these things is causing the next thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.41,1:36:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There we go.\NIt thinks the mind...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.91,1:36:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the way the linear person believes the mind works.\NAnd we've already taken out its underpinnings this morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.80,1:36:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So that what I say next morning...\NThis will make sense to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.64,1:36:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It thinks this is how it's working.\NNow, the Buddha said the ultimate reality is realizable between two thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.52,1:36:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not the best form of expression and I've told him so.\NI said, Buddha buddy, here's the way I look at it.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.54,1:36:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And he agreed, it's better.\NHe said, you got 2,000 years to think about it, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:54.88,1:37:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally, 2,000 years is the only way you can think about it.\NSo, if you meditate like I did when I first read about Zen and started going to Zen Institute and all,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:04.88,1:37:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you start looking between these thoughts.\NYou're waiting for between dog and cat and run up tree there's going to be a little space that you can see God through there.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:14.88,1:37:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to wait a long time, folks, because these flow so fast you can't get between them.\NThere is no space between the thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.13,1:37:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAnd they do not occur this way.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.64,1:37:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if they occur this way, you can't get between them, huh?\NHow does thought really arise?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.06,1:37:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, here's the deliverance from being dominated by the ego.\NEach thought, like creation, arises individually as a separate and individual creation out of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.15,1:38:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of nothingness, out of the great void, which is not the ultimate reality,\Nwhich it was thought by some Hinyana Buddhist.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:02.32,1:38:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the void arises dog, arises cat, arises up, arises tree.\NEach one, each concept is an original creation out of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.22,1:38:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not created out of this.\NThis is not an endless string of billiard balls and you can't get between the two billiard balls.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:26.22,1:38:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Dog comes up, then cat comes up, then up comes up, and then tree comes up.\NAnd this is silence.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.78,1:38:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of silence, each thought arises as an original creation.\NIf you watch your thinkingness, then, instead of watching for this linear sequence,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.51,1:39:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,saying, oh, God, please help me forget about how I let old Rover get hit by the car,\Nthat's this whole long sequence.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.30,1:39:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll see that the thought is coming up piecemeal.\NFirst, this component, out of a silent nothingness void,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:08.30,1:39:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,arises this as an original creation.\NIf the basis of existence was causality,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.48,1:39:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you would not be able to interrupt the train of thought\Nbecause the train of thought is continuous and goes on forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.84,1:39:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no break in a train of thought.\NThe reason you can break through it is because this thought is not caused by this thought at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:38.08,1:39:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one of these thoughts arises independently,\Nand from here down, the mind is silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.47,1:39:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, 99% of this mind is silent, empty,\Nand each thought now arises independently.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:59.32,1:40:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that they take some kind of a meaningful form\Nis because within consciousness there are certain designs,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:12.91,1:40:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,certain designs which have been made famous by an English scientist\Nwhose name I can't think of at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:21.71,1:40:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The things before they exist within the physical domain\Nalready exist within consciousness as a pattern waiting for expression.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.32,1:40:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You got it, Rupert Sheldrake's Morphic Fields.\NAll right, so the Morphic Fields then exist within consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:42.15,1:40:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So out of silence, within consciousness,\Nthere's a million patterns created by mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:40:49.21,1:40:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,so that the potentiality for form exists\Nand this already is like a blueprint of energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:56.21,1:41:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That's our karmic pattern.\NAnd within consciousness, there is the potentiality of all these various forms.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:04.21,1:41:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so if you think you are this,\Nthen you are in for a tough life,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:10.69,1:41:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,which is 99% of people on the planet.\NIf you realize that you are this,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:17.43,1:41:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,then you realize your mind is silent\Nbecause to go from silence into form
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.46,1:41:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,requires intention, intention.\NAnd here you can catch that all thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,1:41:31.72,1:41:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is coming out of your personal intention to think\Nbecause you become hypnotized and fascinated
Dialogue: 0,1:41:39.48,1:41:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,with thinkingness itself.\NAll right, you can catch this in meditation.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.84,1:41:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You can catch this in meditation.\NYou look at a tone of music.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.03,1:41:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, as a tone of music, as the note is struck,\Nit rises to your attention.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.03,1:42:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But as the note of music rises to your attention,\Nit's already beginning to fall, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:04.03,1:42:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It only is at the peak for a split 10,000th of a second.\NNo sooner has a tone of music become apparent to the ear
Dialogue: 0,1:42:12.38,1:42:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,than it's already falling away.\NSo every experience can be viewed as a wave.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:18.48,1:42:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,People who live in fear\Nthen are always trying to anticipate
Dialogue: 0,1:42:28.20,1:42:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the front of the wave.\NThe experience comes up and then it's gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:33.23,1:42:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people are always trying to get one up on the next instant.\NFearful, they're constantly on guard, paranoid, fearful,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.23,1:42:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to control everything.\NSo they don't live in the joy of the present.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:45.23,1:42:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,They live in the fear of the future\Nand constantly trying to control.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.23,1:42:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What will I say when he says this?\NWhat will I wear? What will people think?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:53.48,1:42:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Which way shall I turn?\NWhat will happen if I run out of insurance?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:56.48,1:42:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What if they fire me?\NThey just live on the fear of the future.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.48,1:43:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So they're living in advance of the wave of reality.\NHow can you experience reality
Dialogue: 0,1:43:03.48,1:43:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,which is only experiential on the crest of the wave\Nwhen you're focused on the front of the wave, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.48,1:43:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,People hang into the past.\NThere are other people who ruminate all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.44,1:43:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,They never live on the crest of now\Nbecause they're always reworking what happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.83,1:43:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I should have said this. I'll show that guy.\NNext time he tries that with me,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:29.83,1:43:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I mean?\NYou're trying to rewrite history.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:33.83,1:43:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,All the people busy in the academic world now\Nare trying to rewrite history.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:42.04,1:43:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,To live on the crest of the moment\Nmeans the willingness to relinquish
Dialogue: 0,1:43:47.04,1:43:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the willfulness of editorializing about experience.\NThe human's will is to editorialize,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:57.44,1:44:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,constantly change shape and control the experience.\NEither try to fool reality by anticipating it
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.70,1:44:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,or refuse to let go of it by clinging to it.\NSo the technique of meditation
Dialogue: 0,1:44:15.33,1:44:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that brings you into an awareness of the presence as silence\Nis the willingness to surrender each thing as it arises.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:23.65,1:44:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The surrenderingness is as each thing peaks into awareness.\NAs it arises, we surrender it to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:34.07,1:44:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to surrender\Neverything to God as it comes into awareness.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.07,1:44:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, if you keep doing that,\Nyou get earlier and earlier in the pattern of thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:44.29,1:44:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to catch it here at Sheldrakes.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:48.29,1:44:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't think of his name at this point.\NYou begin to catch it here as it begins to take form.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:53.48,1:45:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,As it begins to take form.\NBecause thoughts are not unlike the rest of creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:00.57,1:45:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Each species, each genus comes off the evolutionary branch.\NSeparately.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.18,1:45:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't see links between the various branches.\NIt comes off as this and then it comes off as that.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:19.88,1:45:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But you don't see any evolutionary half-zebra, half-horse.\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:25.88,1:45:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The zebra comes off, the horse comes off.\NNeanderthal man comes off, magnetoman comes off.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:31.72,1:45:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But you don't see evolution as a slow progression\Nfrom one genus and species into another.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:40.78,1:45:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What you see is the advancement on the stem of life energy itself.\NIt emerges as this and then more advanced as this
Dialogue: 0,1:45:48.88,1:45:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and then more advanced as that.\NSo homo sapien is not an improvement on chromomagnon man.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:58.67,1:46:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He's something different.\NHe's not an improvement on Neanderthal man.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:02.67,1:46:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't see Neanderthal man slowly becoming homo sapien.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:08.67,1:46:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one comes off separately.\NEach one is a different expression of Sheldrake's morphogenetic field.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:19.50,1:46:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolution occurs on the level of consciousness.\NThen it manifests out as an expression of the form
Dialogue: 0,1:46:27.60,1:46:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that is held within consciousness.\NSo the evolution of form then happens on the level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:46:34.60,1:46:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and then expresses itself within the manifest, visible,\Ndomain.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:41.65,1:46:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That brings up an interesting conundrum,\Nwhich I haven't figured out yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:46.81,1:46:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Who was the mother of the first human being,\Nthe first homo sapien?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:53.06,1:47:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if each branch doesn't become the next branch,\Nsuddenly there's a new branch called homo sapien.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:00.06,1:47:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Who was the mother of the first human being?\NIt wasn't an ape because evolution doesn't occur out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:06.16,1:47:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It occurs on the level of consciousness.\NWhy do we humans even get ourselves born?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:15.16,1:47:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, not only are we born, but we've got no fur.\NSeventy man finds himself born with no fur.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:23.19,1:47:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell do you do?\NNo clothes and no fur.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:27.25,1:47:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No hooves.\NHow do you walk across the desert with these kind of feet?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:31.25,1:47:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me that.\NYou can't climb rocks.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:37.56,1:47:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What can he do?\NHe hasn't got wings to fly.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:39.56,1:47:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a pathetic creature, isn't he?\NStark naked, no fur, no wings, no claws.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:44.60,1:47:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,No big teeth.\NNo hooves.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:48.60,1:47:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're supposed to survive.\NOh, boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:51.88,1:47:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We were the losers in some big crap game, weren't we?\NYou get no fur.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:58.20,1:48:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You get no clothes.\NYou get no money when you get there.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:00.20,1:48:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No hooves, no paws.\NNo friends, no mama, no daddy.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:05.68,1:48:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right, we're trying to transcend the mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:13.47,1:48:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Things I'm saying are not irrelevant to the ultimate conclusion,\Nwhich is your enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:17.47,1:48:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Because these are the blocks which prevent it.\NThe belief in duality.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:23.47,1:48:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Not realizing that just holding on to a positionality\Nis creating all the noise in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:27.47,1:48:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinking that your confrontation is that you have to transcend\Nthis entire mind where you don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:32.47,1:48:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,98% of your mind is gone already.\NThat's the good news.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:41.50,1:48:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.\NIf you watch your mind, then you will see
Dialogue: 0,1:48:44.50,1:48:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that thoughts are originating out of silence.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:48.69,1:48:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look at your mind right now,\Npicture your mind as sort of a space here.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:52.69,1:48:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll see the thinkingness is going on at the very front.\NWords, thinkingness, images, all that.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:58.69,1:49:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Right behind all that is really sort of a feelingness.\NBut then behind all that is really nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:06.84,1:49:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There's really primarily silence.\NOut of which a little wispy thought starts to come out.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:13.88,1:49:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If you encourage it, it'll gain some control.\NIf you don't encourage it, it'll back down again.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:19.00,1:49:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You can actually catch the mind.\NYou'll catch the source of thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,1:49:24.00,1:49:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of an energy field.\NThere's an energy field within the void itself
Dialogue: 0,1:49:29.00,1:49:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,whose narcissistic goal is its own continuation,\Nand it does so by energizing thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:40.44,1:49:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And what you're hooked on and hypnotized by\Nis the thinkingness itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:47.05,1:49:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, hypnotic states can be undone.\NOnce you realize they are a hypnotic state,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:51.05,1:49:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,they cannot be undone if you just think that's reality.\NBut once you realize, and the doctor tells you,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:59.44,1:50:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,you've all been hypnotized without your conscious assent,\Nthen you're in a position to begin to undo it.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:07.53,1:50:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Just to know that you are not your thoughts,\Nthat you are hypnotized in a hypnotic state
Dialogue: 0,1:50:13.53,1:50:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you believe that your thinkingness and thoughts are you.\NIt's not possible for your thinkingness and your thoughts to be you,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:21.84,1:50:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,or you'd be dead long ago.\NNow that, if you weren't dead,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:28.13,1:50:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody would kill you for sure\Nfor what goes on in your thinkingness and your thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:33.13,1:50:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't they?\NNo, your thinkingness and your thoughts are not you,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:38.13,1:50:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,or you couldn't even be here.\NAll right, so you discover.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:42.13,1:50:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now here's how the addiction to the thinkingness\Npropagates itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:51.77,1:50:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Polarity means, then,\Nthat we create a set of,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:56.09,1:51:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,a set of opposites so that that sets up tension,\Ncontention,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:02.12,1:51:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and propagates the illusions of the ego.\NThe way we do this is we are addicted to politicizing things.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:11.12,1:51:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Politicizing.\NYou can't mention anything anymore
Dialogue: 0,1:51:15.12,1:51:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that doesn't get instantly politicized.\NPeople want to either de-genderize everything
Dialogue: 0,1:51:21.72,1:51:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,or genderize it, depending on their political position.\NAnd I say, if you want to de-genderize everything,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:27.82,1:51:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to get into a foreign language\Nwhere everything in the,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:30.82,1:51:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,every single word in the language has a gender.\NThe table, the door.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:36.82,1:51:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you use a feminine or masculine pronoun,\Nso how in the world are you going to de-genderize
Dialogue: 0,1:51:41.82,1:51:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the language in which it is intrinsic to the language?\NOr it moralizes about things,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:47.98,1:51:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,or it idealizes,\Nhypothesizes.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:50.98,1:51:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the bases of death and destruction throughout history.\NWe politicize things,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:55.98,1:52:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we get out the machine guns.\NWe moralize they deserve to die.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:00.98,1:52:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't even feel guilty about it.\NWe idealize what a nice world it would be if they were gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:07.98,1:52:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We hypothesize that they shouldn't be the way they are anyway.\NWe romanticize what a nice world it would be
Dialogue: 0,1:52:14.98,1:52:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,if all the so-and-sos were off the planet.\NAnd we'll help them get off the planet by one form or another.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:22.20,1:52:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The justification and the rationalization for this\Nis to criticize.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:29.22,1:52:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So we criticize.\NWe polarize.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:32.64,1:52:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We get ourselves in quite a state and emotionalize about it.\NAnd then we dramatize it.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:37.73,1:52:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a drama.\NWe have a protest.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:39.73,1:52:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We parade with flags.\NDown with the whatchamacallits.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:43.76,1:52:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Down with the professional protesters.\NYou know, the FBI takes pictures of all these protests.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:48.76,1:52:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see people there at every protest about everything.\NThey have the sign at home that says down with,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:53.76,1:52:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and they leave that blank.\NPut in there down with Clinton,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:57.76,1:53:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,down with Bush,\Ndown with animal rights,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:00.76,1:53:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,down with God knows what,\Ndown with dogs.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:04.92,1:53:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And they tend to dramatize it\Nand that justifies catastrophizing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:08.92,1:53:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Catastrophizing it.\NOur society is now in a catastrophe.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:13.92,1:53:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Our society has been in a continuous catastrophe\Nsince man began.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:18.92,1:53:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Man's history is one continuous catastrophe\Nif you look at it in a certain way.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:24.18,1:53:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It started with a catastrophe.\NNo fur, no claws, no hoofs.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:28.18,1:53:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you know, no mother.\NWho is the human being's first mother?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:32.60,1:53:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish that everybody would puzzle on that one.\NWho could be the first mother?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:36.85,1:53:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Because each one comes off as a new one.\NSo who is the first mother then
Dialogue: 0,1:53:40.98,1:53:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,if it didn't evolve from a prior biped?\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:44.98,1:53:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So we theorize about it,\Njust as I'm doing right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:48.40,1:53:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So we theorize it.\NWell, it could have been a...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:51.40,1:53:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we rationalize our behavior.\NWe fantasize.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:55.40,1:53:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We infantilize everything.\NOur society is greatly damaged.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:59.40,1:54:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody is infantilizing.\NNobody is responsible for anything anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:04.48,1:54:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,If you hit your head against the door,\Nyou sue the doormaker.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:08.74,1:54:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,If your building gets bombed,\Nyou sue people that your building is bombable.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:14.74,1:54:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the latest kick.\NThat your building is bombable.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:19.77,1:54:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo you fantasize.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:23.00,1:54:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You infantilize people.\NYou intellectualize.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:27.00,1:54:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't have to feel negative about things.\NYou intellectualize how right it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:31.00,1:54:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And you mentalize.\NWe idealize twice.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:35.64,1:54:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We idealize twice because it's so important.\NThen we glamorize.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:40.67,1:54:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be weird when they show up twice.\NAnd then we glamorize everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:45.70,1:54:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the great world of the media.\NThe great media add to the hypnotic trance.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:51.70,1:54:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody is in a hypnotic trance.\NAnd the media know that.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:55.70,1:55:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So therefore, you don't have to have any...\NThe basic dictum now is no reality is necessary.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:00.70,1:55:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it's an impediment.\NKnowing that it counts is the image.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:05.56,1:55:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The image that is the total message.\NYou don't need any reality at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:11.63,1:55:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can create...\NOh, I'll create a product right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:15.63,1:55:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Grabhams.\NBig red box.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:20.13,1:55:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Hands coming out.\NChildren's hands.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:22.13,1:55:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Grabhams.\NNow, it doesn't matter what you put in the box, does it?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:26.58,1:55:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Crunchies, creepies, pink and blue little crunchies.\NDoesn't matter what you put in the box
Dialogue: 0,1:55:31.58,1:55:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,because you already got a product.\NYour product is the grabhams.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:35.54,1:55:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Grabhams make you happy.\NGrabhams make you healthy.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:38.54,1:55:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Grabhams build better humans, Americans.\NYou can build up a whole product called grabhams.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:44.54,1:55:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And you don't even know what the product is yet.\NThat's the last part of the...
Dialogue: 0,1:55:47.54,1:55:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,When you get the whole production put together,\Nyou say, what are we going to put in the box?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:50.54,1:55:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NPut the little crunchy things.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:53.54,1:55:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the last minute.\NDoesn't require...
Dialogue: 0,1:55:56.54,1:56:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can glamorize things.\NBeautiful people eat grabhams.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:00.54,1:56:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Strong people eat grabhams.\NPeople with great abs.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:04.54,1:56:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Great abs.\NPeople with big biceps like mine.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:11.33,1:56:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,People with a full head of hair.\NDemonizing is the specialty of the current media
Dialogue: 0,1:56:20.79,1:56:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's the one you really got to watch.\NIt can't seem to like vanilla without hating chocolate.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:27.33,1:56:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The current political bent, editorial bent is\Nyou can't just like something,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:34.33,1:56:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to hate the other one.\NSo we said last night,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:38.00,1:56:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the fact that you love vanilla\Ndoesn't mean you have to hate chocolate.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:42.00,1:56:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that you like chocolate\Ndoesn't mean you have to hate vanilla.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:45.00,1:56:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You can tell me what's great about your candidate.\NYou don't have to demonize the other one.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:50.10,1:56:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?\NIf you don't have anything good to say about yourself,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:53.10,1:57:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,then all you can do is demonize the opponent.\NPeople spend all their time demonizing the opponent.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:00.41,1:57:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I say they must not have anything good to offer\Nbecause all they can do is knock the other guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:05.41,1:57:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But what have you got to offer?\NYou know?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:08.41,1:57:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What is your solution to man's problems?\NAnd then they go silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:11.41,1:57:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't have any.\NAll right, so we demonize.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:14.80,1:57:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We prize things and we seek them out.\NAnd of course, victimizing is of course
Dialogue: 0,1:57:20.80,1:57:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the great basis of current society.\NEverything and everyone is the victim of something else.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:29.50,1:57:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have the world of perpetrator and victim\Nwhich is the ultimate expression
Dialogue: 0,1:57:35.60,1:57:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of the basic belief in causality.\NAs long as you believe in causality,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:40.92,1:57:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,there will always be a perpetrator and a victim.\NAnd you will never find the answer to anything
Dialogue: 0,1:57:47.46,1:57:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,because neither one is so.\NThose are both imaginations projected out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:52.46,1:58:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The closest thing to the truth I've seen in the media then\Nwas the discovery of that headline
Dialogue: 0,1:58:01.89,1:58:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that said that the accident of that,\Nwhat do you call those spaceships?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:06.89,1:58:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Shuttle.\NShuttle, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:09.18,1:58:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Was the consequence of the culture,\Nnow they're getting close.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:13.24,1:58:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the first thing I've heard that's close to reality\Nthat's crossed the public view.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:18.24,1:58:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the culture.\NIt's the totality of the field that allows that to happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:24.24,1:58:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as you're looking for Mr. X\Nwho forgot to screw in the jiggly thing so we can sue him,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:29.24,1:58:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you're never going to find it\Nbecause he's only the expression of the totality of the culture
Dialogue: 0,1:58:35.24,1:58:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,which all of us grab a little from the till,\Nall of us scoop a little off the bottom,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:40.31,1:58:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,all of us, you know what I mean?\NIt's the culture that allows that.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:44.31,1:58:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see whole societies and countries bogged down\Nbecause of the culture, the culture.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:53.20,1:59:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What went on in Chicago when I was a kid,\NI don't know if it still goes on,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:00.12,1:59:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but the culture, the culture allowed for certain variances\Nwith what we would call the perfect ideal.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:09.60,1:59:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And somebody I knew,\NI used to come down and see him in Chicago,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:16.96,1:59:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and he'd park right in front of the hydrant.\NI'd say, hey, you're going to get a ticket.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:22.19,1:59:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, no, the cop and I are friends,\Nyou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:26.19,1:59:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,In that culture, at that time, in that neighborhood,\Nthat's the way things went, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:31.19,1:59:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the way things went.\NWe see whole cultures in which that's how it goes.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:37.19,1:59:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The police pull you over not because you're violating the law,\Nbut because they got you and it's going to cost you to get off.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:44.44,1:59:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And the judge knows that, so he gets a slice,\Nso God help you if you've been a defender in certain countries
Dialogue: 0,1:59:50.86,1:59:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's going to cost you plenty to get it back.\NYou're under arrest for so and so,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:55.86,2:00:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the hand's out there.\NSo that's endemic to the culture.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:00.08,2:00:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the culture.\NIt's the whole space that allows that.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:03.08,2:00:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't him being a bad guy,\Ndoing a bad thing against a bad guy,
Dialogue: 0,2:00:07.08,2:00:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's causality.\NIt's the totality of the field.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:11.08,2:00:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So we as spiritually evolving people then\Nare actually changing the field.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:16.66,2:00:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We're actually changing the field.\NA field that went up from 190 to 207 is a different field.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:22.66,2:00:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,In 207, you can't just comfortably pay off the local cops anymore.\NYou can't comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:28.76,2:00:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He isn't comfortable about it anymore.\NThere's a certain lap over between the old way and the new way.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:33.76,2:00:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a period of discomfort.\NThe guys who are used to it the old way
Dialogue: 0,2:00:38.11,2:00:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,don't want to, you know, go against their old friends.\NThe new guys don't want to make it hard on the old guys.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:44.11,2:00:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So you get a sort of a painful adjustment\Nwhere you're lapping over from one culture
Dialogue: 0,2:00:49.11,2:00:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,into a new culture.\NAnd people, opportunists, try to seize the new culture
Dialogue: 0,2:00:59.13,2:01:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and retrograde, project it against the old culture\Nand do a make wrong on what would happen in history.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:05.48,2:01:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened in history?\NThe relationship of men and women
Dialogue: 0,2:01:09.48,2:01:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in our socioeconomic state is different in 2003\Nthan it was in 1930.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:15.96,2:01:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't take the social structure of 2003\Nand go back to 1930 and say,
Dialogue: 0,2:01:23.92,2:01:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,look how wrong it was.\NThat was an agrarian, rural culture.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:29.44,2:01:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We all had our family roles\Nbased on the nature of society at that time.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:35.44,2:01:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,To take some political agenda\Nprojected backward in time and do a make wrong,
Dialogue: 0,2:01:39.98,2:01:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you see how you're no longer dealing in reality at all.
